<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><gpx xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:groundspeak="http://www.groundspeak.com/cache/1/0/1" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" version="1.0" creator="Groundspeak, Inc.All Rights Reserved.http://www.groundspeak.com" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.topografix.com/GPX/1/0 http://www.topografix.com/GPX/1/0/gpx.xsd http://www.groundspeak.com/cache/1/0/1 http://www.groundspeak.com/cache/1/0/1/cache.xsd" xmlns="http://www.topografix.com/GPX/1/0"><name>Cache Listing Generated from Geocaching.com</name><desc>This is an individual cache generated from Geocaching.com</desc><email>contact@geocaching.com</email><url>http://www.geocaching.com</url><urlname>Geocaching - High Tech Treasure Hunting</urlname><time>2026-06-02T21:38:51.679829Z</time><keywords>cache, geocache</keywords><wpt lat="35.607367" lon="-97.6095"><time>2025-01-02T00:00:00</time><name>GC9JQCP</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Oklahoma by CacheSleuth</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC9JQCP</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Oklahoma</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="8459304" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Oklahoma</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>CacheSleuth</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="14688044">CacheSleuth</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="0">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="47" inc="1">Field puzzle</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="0">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="51" inc="1">Special tool required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="60" inc="1">Wireless beacon</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Oklahoma</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/078c6545-c107-4d96-b1de-870b357c26ad.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/b70de011-9278-4c56-b2c2-7fdb06ad6618_l.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="font-size:1.3em;"&gt;Welcome to Cache Odyssey - Oklahoma! This cache is one of the 9 caches in the &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2" target="_blank"&gt;Cache Odyssey GeoTour - South Region (GT4F2)&lt;/a&gt;, which is part of a 50 state series of letterbox hybrid caches that are wheelchair accessible and have a regular sized container OR LARGER. Every cache in this series is a well thought out, highly creative experience designed for you, the cacher, to enjoy. If you get a chance to visit others in this series (6 GeoTours in all), I highly recommend making it a priority in your plans! More information about the project can be found at the bottom of this cache page.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;

&lt;H2 style="text-align:center;"&gt;HOURS OF AVAILABILITY&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;BR /&gt;

&lt;p style="font-size:1.3em;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;This geocache is only available Wednesday - Sunday&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;. From November 1st to March 31st, it is available from 8am to 4:30pm. From April 1st to October 31st, it is available from 9am to 5:30pm. It is closed on all federal holidays. Please see the &lt;a href="https://www.okc.gov/Community-Recreation/OKC-Parks/Martin-Park-Nature-Center"&gt;park website&lt;/a&gt; for more information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p style="font-size:1.3em;"&gt;Before we get started, &lt;b&gt;you must have a smartphone with internet access&lt;/b&gt; in order to complete this cache. If you arrive without this item, you will need to make friends with a stranger passing by who has one because you won't be able to proceed. Are we on the same page here? Okay good. &lt;img src="/images/icons/icon_smile.gif" border="0" align="middle" /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Since this is a letterbox hybrid, the container has a stamp inside of it that &lt;span style="color:red;"&gt;stays with the geocache itself&lt;/span&gt;. You may stamp the logbook with your personal stamp or if you don't letterbox, that's okay, you can just sign the logbook, no problem. If you would like to keep track of your progress of the tour, you can print out the &lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Cache-Odyssey-South-GeoTour-Passport.pdf"&gt;GeoTour Passport&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt; and use this stamp to fill in the Oklahoma spot! I also have some passports printed in the cache for your convenience. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;font-size:1em;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/fd07a4b2-0a49-49f3-a4d4-fbbc2335c136_l.jpg" /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Sign at the posted coordinates.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="font-size:1.3em;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;TO FIND THE GEOCACHE:&lt;/b&gt; At the posted coordinates, you will see the above signage. On the back of this, you will find a smaller blue sign with 8 words written on it in white letters. &lt;u&gt;Enter the last three words into the checker below.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;B&gt;Read everything in the checker&lt;/B&gt; as the information contained within will guide you on what is needed to access the geocache!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:1.3em;font-family:monospace;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;------------ ------ -------&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The words match this pattern.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div style="text-align:center;"&gt;
&lt;a href="https://www.certitudes.org/certitude?wp=GC9JQCP"&gt;
&lt;img src="https://www.certitudes.org/logo?wp=GC9JQCP" title="Click to see the list of solvers" style="filter:drop-shadow(3px 3px 3px #CCC);" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;div style="font-family:Comic Sans MS;"&gt;You can validate your puzzle solution with &lt;a href="https://www.certitudes.org/certitude?wp=GC9JQCP"&gt;certitude&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p style="font-size:1.3em;"&gt;This cache was placed here by permission from the park staff. You do not need to interact with them to complete this experience (though they might be excited to watch you figure it out &lt;img src="/images/icons/icon_smile.gif" border="0" align="middle" /&gt;). If you need help, please reach out to me via &lt;a href="https://www.geocaching.com/account/messagecenter?recipientId=4896476a-9fd1-413e-8cf0-a0e909ec18e5&amp;amp;gcCode=GC9JQCP" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;b&gt;geocaching messages&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and I will get back to you as soon as possible. If you want to send me a message before you arrive to let me know when you are going, I will try my best to be available to assist via messages if needed when you are there. Happy caching! &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the South Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b19ba586-1a55-44b3-8eb2-0781c0a8e99a.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Retired Guy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.RetiredGuy.com/CacheOdyssey.html" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;img alt="Cache Odyssey Leaderboard" src="https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/hm6bipgl0xa4028mlasov/CacheOdysseySouth.jpg?rlkey=omo44cgp0htkxl1zf2iu60qaf&amp;amp;st=vr963f9l&amp;amp;raw=1" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/c20b8f24-2486-4074-bd9a-5bc88f0d1d6b.jpg" style="width:100%;max-width:100%;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>The riddle rhymes with the answer. Attributes may help. Note: This cache is only accessible Wednesday - Sunday. From 11/1 to 3/31, 8am to 4:30pm and from 4/1 to 10/31, 9am to 5:30pm. It is closed on all federal holidays.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364720076"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T15:09:47</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6744281">KoolWaters</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This took a minute fof my brain to catch up
Picking a few fave caches, some Nat Parks and a few rest areas as I make my way home to San Diego.
Thanks, CacheSleuth for placing this cache!
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363915056"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T13:16:08</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1670110">Paddling Pirates</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">In the area for GeoWoodstock XXII. Had a great time at all the official events and now doing some stuff on our own. Thanks for placing this geocache. 

Glad to have this one off our bucket list. It was a fun one.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363916511"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T13:14:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="391008">dcdawn</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Visiting from Wisconsin. Today I was headed from Stillwater to Elk City via eight or so geo-stops, including the OK Cache Odyssey. 

This one had me flummoxed. I sat on a (comfortable!) bench for a long time getting a step or two closer to my prize. I reached out to the CO, who confirmed I was on the right track. Then I continued sitting and wracking my brain. The park manager paused to give me another hint and I was closer. I headed back to the cache and saw two other cachers had arrived. SAVED!!! Paddling Pirates found the last piece to the puzzle and I was soon (very happily) signing the log. Thanks for a diabolically clever cache…and thanks to all those who helped me on my quest.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363466655"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2784112">HarborSpy</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found with the GA HICs while on our grand GWX expedition. TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364218065"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="20237966">TJ</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">It’s GeoWoodstock XXII weekend! Queenie and I put more than 2,100 miles on her Cache Carriage driving from Minnesota to the Mega event in Henderson, Kansas. Along the way, we celebrated milestones, reunited with old friends, made a bunch of new ones, and collected a huge number of quality geocaches. Five straight days of geocaching fun from start to finish!

Day Four was all about a geocaching day trip into Oklahoma, marking my very first time caching in the state! And we definitely made the most of it! We tackled Oklahoma’s oldest, completed another Cache Odyssey, conquered The Infernal Device, and even scored an FTF along the way. Add in a healthy collection of counties, challenge caches, and plenty of other geo-goodies, and it turned into an unforgettable day of adventure on the back (and main) roads of Oklahoma!

We checked, double, and triple checked to make sure this would be available today. And huzzah – it was! We enjoyed working through the stages, and I liked the twist at the end. A nice combination of techniques that I hadn’t seen combined quite like this! Thanks for the fun!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="33.12588" lon="-96.089485"><time>2024-10-31T00:00:00</time><name>GCAZV9M</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Texas by gslinkandslinkymama</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCAZV9M</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Texas</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9743105" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Texas</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>gslinkandslinkymama</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="617318">gslink</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="53" inc="1">Park and grab</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Texas</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/078c6545-c107-4d96-b1de-870b357c26ad.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Audie Murphy/American Cotton Museum&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At stage one, what number do you see?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1. 400 - Cache is over by the horse you see when you drove up.&lt;br /&gt;
2. 600 - Cache is inside the gift shop.&lt;br /&gt;
3. 800 - Cache is due west of the parking lot over by the barbwire fence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Final clue: it&amp;#39;s Latin Name is a Tautonym&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/0dabea54-40c0-43c6-92ca-afbf31532276.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:13.5pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;History of Cotton Exhibit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Discover the days of a bygone era when cotton was a part of everyday life in Hunt County. Greenville was home to the world’s largest inland cotton compress, which set a world record both in 1911 and 1912. Imagine in just one 10 hour work day being able to compress 2,073 bales of cotton! The engine of the compress is on display at the Museum.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h4 style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:13.5pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hunt County War Memorial&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;A ten foot bronze statue of Audie Murphy sculpted by Greenville artist Gordon Thomas stands vigil over the war memorial that was dedicated in 2004 to honor the memory of the 271 soldiers of Hunt County who gave their lives to protect and defend the United States in times of war during the 20th Century. As Audie Murphy once stated “The true heroes, the real heroes, are the boys who fought and died, and never will come home.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:13.5pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Museum Hours&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Open Tuesday – Saturday 10:00a.m. – 5:00p.m.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Closed Sundays, Mondays and major holidays.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://cottonmuseum.com/" style="text-decoration:none;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#1155cc;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Audie Murphy/American Cotton Museum&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" style="width:80%;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the South Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/76de9cdc-8b3c-4816-8280-2fbc61852b60.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/18d9b309-a90c-4900-a735-2eedd7912009.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/0f404634-c476-4cd5-b8df-f85d6aa8069e.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/dc93f2f7-97ae-4cb4-a9e1-8986f081414f.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/179e8963-86e3-49a1-bc17-fd28c53b735a.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/f6ab1d02-9794-4521-955f-0bcf19e3c566.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/ba935c3f-3961-459a-a950-8b1462cbe818.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.RetiredGuy.com/CacheOdyssey.html" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;img alt="Cache Odyssey Leaderboard" src="https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/hm6bipgl0xa4028mlasov/CacheOdysseySouth.jpg?rlkey=omo44cgp0htkxl1zf2iu60qaf&amp;amp;st=vr963f9l&amp;amp;raw=1" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>large and white lettering</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364244079"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T15:40:43</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="95396">Me &amp; Bucky</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Bucky &amp; I found this one with Moose Mob on an amazing day of caching. The temp was in the low 90s in a cloudy, warm, muggy day.  

This is Day 19 on our trip to GeoWoodstock XXII!   Stayed in Marshall, Texas last night, and now working a bit on 2-step counties in the northeast part of the state.  

Great stop here at the museum!  Made the quick find, then continued on for more fun.  

Thanks for the cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364257085"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T15:38:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="205965">Moose Mob</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Proud member of the coordinate verification and pencil distribution team.

Great place to visit.

Wandering across Northeastern Texas with me &amp; Bucky, finding a few geocaches along the way. Watering coronavirus bushes and irritating the gophers!

[Nevada Geocaching](http://www.facebook.com/groups/337489309623791/)
[Geocachers of Mesquite Nevada](https://www.facebook.com/groups/333103173116062)
