[Bay Area Geocachers](https://www.facebook.com/groups/BayAreaGeocachers)
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363883900"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="48318008">dobiest</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Quick find here on my first journey through this area of the country. This was a nice museum and very friendly staff who heard all about Geocaching from my travel pal Troopbiz. TFTC SL </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363878912"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2464712">Troopbiz</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">**Cache Odyssey - Texas**
**Find #22833**
**Cache Odyssey #23**

**About This Cache**
DOBIEST and I have really been enjoying our journey across America working on the Cache Odyssey series, and we are nearing the halfway point following a deep south spree on the way home from GeoWoodstock XXII. A strategic plan was made to fly out of Dallas in the afternoon, which meant we had just enough time to add this one to the list!

Perhaps it was fate, or perhaps it was just good planning, but we dodged all the Memorial Day restrictions and closed hours of operations to find this one at 10 am when they opened. It worked out perfectly, considering it was about a 4-hour drive from where we stayed last night and 2 hours from the airport. The museum was even open a few minutes earlier than expected, which provided a much-needed bathroom break.

Enjoyed exploring the grounds and museum. The staff was very interested in the series and our travels so far. I really enjoyed the final container - Bizzzzzzzon are one of my favorite animals. Thanks for this great addition to the series! TFTC SL FP

**About My Trip**
Wrapping up our GeoWoodstock adventure with a final stretch through Texas as we depart from Dallas, but not without stopping for some counties. This is my second time in Texas, and a great opportunity to grab the Cache Odyssey and oldest for the Lone Star State. All logs are signed “TB” or “Troopbiz”. Thanks, gslink, for placing and maintaining this cache! TFTC SL</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363812312"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="505582">emilierene</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found this cache as a part of a Triple Jasmer GeoWoodstock road trip through Texas, Oklahoma, Kansas, Nebraska, Missouri, and Arkansas with Steelers Chic. This was our 4th Cache Odyssey of the trip and my 7th overall.  It was fun to spot the cool camo at the final. Very well done. Thanks for being a part of our memories!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="39.049633" lon="-95.6771"><time>2024-12-02T00:00:00</time><name>GCAXQRX</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Kansas by Nicooole</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCAXQRX</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Kansas</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9681113" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Kansas</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Nicooole</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1599648">Nicooole</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="65" inc="1">Yard (private residence)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="52" inc="0">Night cache</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="14" inc="0">Recommended at night</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="59" inc="1">Food nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="1">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="26" inc="1">Public transportation nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Kansas</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/658927b0-9a5b-4e7d-866f-3f28bcfc6995.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:&amp;amp;quot;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please read here first before attempting this cache&lt;/strong&gt;. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Access to this cache has some limited availability. It is generally open Monday - Friday 8:00 AM - 5:00 PM and closed major holidays. Please check the &lt;a href="https://library.ks.gov/about-us/about"&gt;website https://library.ks.gov/about-us/about&lt;/a&gt;.  For parking in the area please&lt;a href="https://www.da.ks.gov/fm/buildings/information/visitorparking.htm"&gt; click here &lt;/a&gt;for more information. &lt;strong&gt; The scribes here are awesome and know about the cache but they will not help you find it.&lt;/strong&gt;  You will have to follow the instructions carefully. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Permission has been granted to hide this cache as it is hidden&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:&amp;amp;quot;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span dir="auto"&gt;This is a letterbox hybrid geocache containing the Cache Odyssey Kansas self-inking stamp, a stamp pad, and a logbook. If you have a personal stamp, please stamp the logbook with your stamp. You can just sign the logbook if you don&amp;#39;t have a personal stamp. Please leave the stamp and in the letterbox hybrid for the next visitor to use.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:&amp;amp;quot;"&gt;Before we begin the journey visit the posted coordiantes and let me know the last name of this Pioneer Doctor from Kansas. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.certitudes.org/certitude?wp=GCAXQRX"&gt;&lt;img src="https://www.certitudes.org/logo?wp=GCAXQRX" title="Click to see the list of solvers" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;div style="font-family:Comic Sans MS;"&gt;You can validate your puzzle solution with &lt;a href="https://www.certitudes.org/certitude?wp=GCAXQRX"&gt;certitude&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:&amp;amp;quot;"&gt;Starting at your new coordinates head due south. You will come across some ornate wooden doors. Once inside please do what the very nice agents ask you to do. &lt;strong&gt;Do not ask them about the cache they can not help you, just tell them you are visiting.&lt;/strong&gt;  Just make sure not to bring any thing dangerous with you. Keep heading south once in the building you will pass the visitors center. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:&amp;amp;quot;"&gt;Head south through the hallway.  You want to make your way to the third floor. My favorite way is to take the first set of stairs/elevator to the first floor and then take the &lt;strong&gt;Official State Cage Elevator (KS Stat § 73-3501)&lt;/strong&gt; to the 3rd floor. Once you make your way to the third floor head to the north and and find this treasure sitting on the bottom shelf to your right, as you enter into the room. You are looking for a large red leather treasure chest.  &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.da.ks.gov/fm/buildings/information/visitorparking.htm#Harrison%20Street"&gt;Parking information for the Topeka Capitol.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Midwest Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/9513b58f-0611-4f7b-8598-f5b685afca75.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;RetiredGuy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364471734"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1296571">sqirts</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">our first cache odyssey and it was a fun adventure.   thanks for this  SL</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364356696"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T08:52:57</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="10945236">pw621</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Second visit to Topeka. Had to come back for this one during regular hours. Did the capitol dome tour and then went through security a second time! Fun cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364247152"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T15:59:04</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1639892">Uncle Fuzzy</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Gal &amp; I had just found out about the Odyssey caches last year. We have done around a dozen of them I think. Now I’m not sure but I’m willing to bet this is by far the best one in the country. I can’t thank you enough for bringing us here. I am a retired Mason and done a lot of restoration work on New Jersey’s Capitol Building in Trenton, and the original Governor’s Mansion in Princeton. I was so impressed by the workmanship here. This building is a work of art. Too bad I can’t give this cache 100 favorite points.[:D] TFTF .</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364675525"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="10325973">SmithGen3</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thamks</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364265282"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="96095">GuentherGal</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found with Chuck while on a seven month road trip doing some major exploring. Today we were making our way from Cottonwood Falls to Topeka. After getting the rig set up at Shawnee Lake, we made our way over to check out Cache Odyssey - Kansas. After parking, we followed the mysterious directions, encountered the "agents," and took the historic cage elevator to our destination. We had so much fun on that, we rode it a couple more times!

We located the correct room very quickly, and were soon signing in. We then spent the next hour touring the different floors admiring the statues, murals, and beauty of this magnificent building. The only disappointing thing is that we missed the last tour by just five minutes. This is definitely my favorite Odyssey cache to date! We sure appreciate your placing this and adding to our amazing adventure. Thanks for the fantastic fun!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="34.866383" lon="-92.118483"><time>2024-11-09T00:00:00</time><name>GCB06Y3</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Arkansas by MathSeeker</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB06Y3</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Arkansas</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9754279" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Arkansas</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>MathSeeker</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1517511">MathSeeker</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Arkansas</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/078c6545-c107-4d96-b1de-870b357c26ad.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This is a &lt;strong&gt;letterbox hybrid&lt;/strong&gt; geocache containing the &lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Arkansas&lt;/strong&gt; self-inking stamp, a stamp pad, and a logbook. &lt;/span&gt;If you have a personal stamp, please stamp the logbook with your stamp. You can just sign the logbook if you don&amp;#39;t have a personal stamp. The stamp and logbook remain in the letterbox hybrid for the next visitor to use. &lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Feel free to trade swag.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Projection&lt;/strong&gt; to the cache - from the posted coordinates go a distance of 93.374188 ft at a bearing of 147.624906°&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lock Combination&lt;/strong&gt; given in Ceritude.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.certitudes.org/certitude?wp=GCB06Y3"&gt;&lt;img src="https://www.certitudes.org/logo?wp=GCB06Y3" title="Click to see the list of solvers" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;div style="font-family:Comic Sans MS;"&gt;You can validate your puzzle solution with &lt;a href="https://www.certitudes.org/certitude?wp=GCB06Y3"&gt;certitude&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style="font-family:Comic Sans MS;"&gt; &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the South Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; – &lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Cache-Odyssey-East-Central-GeoTour-Passports.pdf"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Passport&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; – &lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Cache-Odyssey-Midwest-GeoTour-Passports.pdf"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Passport&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; – &lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Cache-Odyssey-Northeast-GeoTour-Passport.pdf"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Passport&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; – &lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Cache-Odyssey-Northwest-GeoTour-Passport.pdf"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Passport&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; – &lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Cache-Odyssey-South-GeoTour-Passport.pdf"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Passport&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; – &lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Cache-Odyssey-Southwest-GeoTour-Passport.pdf"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Passport&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b19ba586-1a55-44b3-8eb2-0781c0a8e99a.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;RetiredGuy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364260201"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T19:22:11</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1670110">Paddling Pirates</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">In the area on our creative return trip from GeoWoodstock XXII. Had a great time at all the official events and now doing some stuff on our own. Today we are exploring the Hot Springs area.Thanks for placing this geocache. 

Thanks for the special GeoTour cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364054823"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T12:08:35</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="19236640">CrazChik</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found with Geo202 on our way back from GeoWoodstockXXII</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363895453"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T11:25:48</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="55389774">sunflower_samurai_</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found it!! Very easy simple cache, and the folks who work at the commerce are very sweet! Biggest cache i’ve found so far!! Happy Hunting!! 🌻💕</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363780942"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T15:04:22</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1906272">mdsearcher</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Had to wait the downpour but we found it.  Great cache.  TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363719997"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="505582">emilierene</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found this cache as a part of a Triple Jasmer GeoWoodstock road trip through Texas, Oklahoma, Kansas, Nebraska, Missouri, and Arkansas with Steelers Chic. We're also finding Cache Odyssey Caches as we are able. This is the 3rd one of our trip. Great container and set up. Thanks for being a part of our memories!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="41.024717" lon="-96.313983"><time>2024-11-06T00:00:00</time><name>GCB03KB</name><desc>CACHE ODYSSEY  - NEBRASKA by thndrstrck</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB03KB</url><urlname>CACHE ODYSSEY  - NEBRASKA</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9751094" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>CACHE ODYSSEY  - NEBRASKA</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>thndrstrck</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="722399">thndrstrck</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="2" inc="1">Access/parking fee</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="47" inc="1">Field puzzle</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="1">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="46" inc="1">Trucks/RVs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="31" inc="1">Camping nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Nebraska</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/658927b0-9a5b-4e7d-866f-3f28bcfc6995.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e74c3c;"&gt;A DAILY/ANNUAL NEBRASKA STATE PARK PERMIT IS REQUIRED TO ENTER MAHONEY STATE PARK&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The building where this geocache is located is open daily from 8 AM to 8 PM.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here at the Nature Center &amp;amp; Conservatory building you can explore the newly renovated nature center which has live animal exhibits and interactive nature activities. The nature center is connected to the conservatory, where you can see tropical plants and a working greenhouse. You can also enjoy time relaxing in the new serenity garden and birding area.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At the posted coordinates, there are four words on the side of the building to the right of the door, remember the letter count of each word and read on.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will need to explore three areas inside this building to gather the needed information to open the padlock on the geocache container. Those areas are as follow :&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AREA - A - &lt;/strong&gt;From the posted coordinates enter the building through the single door to take the number of steps in the shortest word at the posted coordinates before you STOP, then turn right. Look up on the brick wall and you will see a large wooden sign with the state park logo in the center. How many words are on this sign? Answer = A.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AREA B -&lt;/strong&gt; After completing the task in Area A, Turn to your left and pass through the doors leading into the conservatory room with waterfall and tropical plants. Explore this area with a short stroll along the path. How many wooden bridges are along the path? Answer = B.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AREA C -&lt;/strong&gt; Return to the main hallway(Area A) and walk towards the nature center (other end of the hallway). On your left, you will notice informational signboards about animals. Each of these signboards has a two word title that starts with &amp;quot;Animal&amp;quot;. Using the second word in each title, count the digits of the those words and then divide by the number of informational signboards. Answer = C.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lock combination = ABC&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now that you have the lock combination, you are ready to find the letterbox container. Proceed to the corner of the hallway where the wall of Area A meets the wall to Area B. Here you will find a wooden table that has a hidden cubby hole that holds the containers. To access the cubby hole, LIFT the RIGHT side of the table top board (it is hinged on the left side). Once the cubby hole is accessable, you will find two containers. One container is for tradable items (remember if you take a tradable item, then please leave something of equal value). The second container has the padlock, and holds the logbook and stamp. Be sure to sign/stamp and date the logbook. The second container also has some swag/tradable items.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e74c3c;"&gt;THE STAMP IS TO REMAIN WITH THE LOGBOOK IN THE PADLOCKED CONTAINER AND IS NOT A SWAG/TRADABLE ITEM. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After you stamp/sign and date the logbook, and swapping of tradable items, replace and reset the padlock. Gently place both containers back into the cubby hole before closing the tabletop board to conseal the cubby hole.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The nature center area of the building is only open certain days and times. If it is open, please take some time to explore the exhibits and activities. This area is excellant for kids of all ages.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This cache is placed with the permission of the Mahoney State Park Area Superintendent.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Midwest Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b19ba586-1a55-44b3-8eb2-0781c0a8e99a.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;RetiredGuy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1365023394"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T14:11:13</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="32508601">MustangNewbie</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thank you! Interesting surroundings. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364727292"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T13:53:23</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8041283">thewildroseoftexas</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Pass on $14 per person to ink log</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364397678"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T11:24:02</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="283262">RainbowRachAndCo</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Passing through the area today, visiting from Wisconsin. We stopped for this one along our route, picking up counties as we enjoy our travels.   Nice stop here. Beautiful park!
Thanks for adding to our fun and TFTC!
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364094272"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T15:58:10</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1149235">Nurse 1</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Wow! Nicely done!

Staying for the night. What an awesome park!

Thanks for this interesting cache.

Traveling the country to escape the stifling Savannah heat but it's HOT here, too!

Came to Hutchinson for GWS XXII and now roadtripping to Gilby, picking up Odyssey caches and anything else interesting.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363966427"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T22:59:10</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4239635">Jeph_Gileadite</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This was the third Cache Odyssey cache I found today along with Kansas and Missouri. I love the work modifying the hosts container. Lovely park here; wish I had the time to stay longer.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="33.3947" lon="-104.529117"><time>2024-12-16T00:00:00</time><name>GCAZMXP</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - New Mexico by JRandJuju</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCAZMXP</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - New Mexico</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9737930" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - New Mexico</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>JRandJuju</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="999671">JRandJuju</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="0">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="52" inc="0">Night cache</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="14" inc="0">Recommended at night</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="26" inc="1">Public transportation nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="46" inc="0">Trucks/RVs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="58" inc="1">Fuel nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="31" inc="0">Camping nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="39" inc="1">Thorns</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>New Mexico</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b7be9a3d-4cd6-45a8-a96e-a3a45b233f37.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e74c3c;"&gt;The Museum requests Daylight only Geocaching.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#4e5f70;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;The posted coordinates will take you to a historic plaque&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#4e5f70;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;From this plaque  go West-South-West&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#4e5f70;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;around 240° towards the NW corner of the Main house.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;Will be about 50 steps(122.8ft)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#4e5f70;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;By The Stairs&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;This Hide is placed on the &amp;quot;Historical Society for Southeast New Mexico&amp;quot;  grounds.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;Placed with permission.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;Stamp  your log and  Passport(if you want)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LEAVE THE STAMP IN THE CACHE!  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Southwest Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b19ba586-1a55-44b3-8eb2-0781c0a8e99a.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Retired Guy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;For more information on the museum, click here &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.roswellnmhistory.org/"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#2980b9;"&gt;Historical Society for Southeast New Mexico&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="color:#2980b9;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Museum is open by Appt. only.  To schedule:  call (575) 622-8333 or&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Email; HistoryDirector@outlook.com&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;Placed with permission of Amy McVay Tellez, Exec. Director.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Wooden box</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364260041"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T18:19:23</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="391008">dcdawn</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Visiting from Wisconsin. After driving from Clovis (with a detour to Billy the Kid’s grave site), I was enjoying checking out Roswell. I’m hoping to get most of the SW and all of my remaining NW Cache Odyssey smilies during this road trip. I had plenty of daylight, so I left this cache for last. That paid off as the parking lot was empty and no one was around to watch me walk right by the cache. Grrr. It didn’t take long for me to backtrack and earn my smilie. Thanks for the fun and my odyssey smilie #16.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363557448"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T11:52:03</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="10453479">alienboy51</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFT cool C</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362232115"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-19T18:47:58</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1118584">CelebrationKim</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">On a weeklong Memorial Day trip through TX, NM, OK, and KS. This was of course one of the main targets of the trip. First time in Roswell. Pic of me below at GZ. SL. TFTL!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361868395"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-17T18:30:34</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="609455">Data Wrangler</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found quickly after teaching ground zero this hot but quiet Sunday afternoon. This completes the Southwest Region GeoTour for me. SL, TFTC.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1357388224"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-25T19:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="444416">cyclegreen</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Took me a bit to get that stamp into my collection.
Great day for a hunt, but they all are. Signed log. TFTF!
1,1's to 5,5's each of the 81 has its own magic.
I enjoy all kinds of hides, and I enjoyed finding yours today.
Thanks for getting me outside.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="40.394833" lon="-105.069083"><time>2024-11-05T00:00:00</time><name>GCB02HK</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Colorado by Barasaur</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB02HK</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Colorado</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9750079" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Colorado</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Barasaur</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="530706">Barasaur</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Colorado</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b7be9a3d-4cd6-45a8-a96e-a3a45b233f37.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Welcome to Cache Odyssey Colorado located at the Loveland Library.  Permission for this geocache has been granted by the director of the library.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The final for this cache is located INSIDE the building.  The library is open Mon-Sat from 10:00 to 5:00, a few days longer.  If you want to double check the library&amp;#39;s hours, click here to go to the  &lt;a href="https://www.lovelandpubliclibrary.org/"&gt;Loveland Public Library&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This cache is a letterbox hybrid and contains a stamp. &lt;u&gt;The stamp is NOT a trade item/swag, please leave it in the cache!&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You will need to capture some information from some different sculptures and painting to get the number of the where you will find this cache inside the library.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You need to know the Letter for section and then the number for where to find it on the shelf&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example is &lt;br /&gt;
X&lt;br /&gt;
abc.5&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Start outside at the posted coordinates, do this for &amp;quot;a&amp;quot;. Now head inside to collect the rest of the information you will needX = Inside is a sculpture called &amp;quot;MELANCHOLY MOMENT&amp;quot;.  What is the last letter in the bottom line on the plaque? &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a = How many letters in the the sculptor&amp;#39;s last name of the sculpture outside the front door known as &amp;quot;THE NEED TO KNOW&amp;quot; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;b = In the sculpture &amp;quot;C IS FOR CAT&amp;quot; how many cats are there?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;c = There is a picture of Hanging Lake.  Find the Medium used  What is the number in the alphabet of the second letter? (It was oil)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using this you shold be able to use the card index, or computer to find the section and shelf where you will find the cache.  Hope you enjoyed a small tour of this great library.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Inside the cache is a stamp for your geotour. There is also a stamp there for you to put your geocache name on and stamp as well for a bit extra.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please feel free to use the big stamp to put your cache name and or date on it to enter in the log. You are still welcome to just sign as before as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/206d9cd3-c304-4bd4-aaad-0f421facf2b0.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Southwest Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b19ba586-1a55-44b3-8eb2-0781c0a8e99a.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;RetiredGuy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1365030344"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T13:53:43</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="24511717">kate8kate</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Tftc </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364922132"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1425692">SmileyPanda</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">☺️ At this time, I would like to extend my heart-felt gratitude to each and every cache owner who takes the time to place and maintain these caches. If it were not for your efforts, Geocaching would not be possible.I offer my most humble thanks. This cache is in good condition.  

🙂 I am in Colorado for a few days on vacation and decided to find some Geocaches to flip another state.   I have found this one and also the Odyssey one in Minnesota.  I guess that makes 2 of them.

I was lucky as I was able to  get all the work done and got myself signed into the logbook with only 1 minute to spare before I got kicked out of the library. 

🤗 I signed the log sheet as 'Panda' (or a close variant as such) and did write today's date. I neither took anything nor left anything.

😅 我很喜欢路灯盖

(June 1st 2026), I found 1656 geocaches / attended events / adventure labs or other virtual etc., and 10 for today.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364076035"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T12:51:42</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14688044">CacheSleuth</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Well hello! I was sooooo bummed when we were right up the street basically earlier this year and didn’t get a chance to stop by. We decided to take a family vacation back again and this was a million percent on my must do list. We planned today *around* getting this cache and I’m happy to say it didn’t disappoint. Came in with my daughter to help and we eventually found where we need to go. Happy to log another in this series! I am the CO of the Oklahoma Cache Odyssey and wanted to say you did great with this one! Favorite point for sure! 

----------

Thank you Barasaur for the Letterbox Hybrid! This is my 5352th [:)]

[CacheSleuth.com](https://cachesleuth.com)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363915482"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T12:16:39</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6041752">Winston4Ever</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I’m caching with Lil Devil after attending GeoWoodstock. We flew into Pensacola 8 days ago. Today, we are leaving Broomfield and will cache around until its flight time. I lost my Winston4Ever stamp so I’m using my Team CG stamp. Nicely done! Thanks for the fun! 
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363914466"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T12:12:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="12409">Lil Devil</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Greetings from California. Winston4ever and I are caching from Denver to Cheyenne and back, picking up counties, challenge caches, high favorite points, and anything else that piques our interest.     
    
The cache had been replaced on the wrong shelf so we had a little trouble finding it. Thanks to Barasaur for the fun. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="31.25265" lon="-89.83515"><time>2024-11-13T00:00:00</time><name>GCB0AZX</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Mississippi by SirDrumalot</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB0AZX</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Mississippi</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9758179" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Mississippi</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>SirDrumalot</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="7804861">SirDrumalot</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="47" inc="1">Field puzzle</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="14" inc="1">Recommended at night</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="59" inc="1">Food nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="1">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Mississippi</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:36px;"&gt;Welcome to Mississippi!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/078c6545-c107-4d96-b1de-870b357c26ad.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Downtown Columbia is your destination for &lt;em&gt;Mississippi&amp;#39;s Cache Odyssey Letterbox Hybrid&lt;/em&gt;. There&amp;#39;s a little something here for everyone, especially Traveling Geocachers. Food, Sweets, Boutiques, Art, and Thift Shops are abundant and you are not far from Historic Columbia High School and it&amp;#39;s 10 Time State Champion Marching Band, &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Marching Wildcats!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; Hopefully you have time to check out some of the other Geocaches in and around Columbia while you are here. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This Letterbox Hybrid is placed with permission and you should have no trouble spotting it. There is typically plenty of parking availabe, even if you require Handicap Access. Check the Parking Waypoint for easiest access.You may, or may not, have difficulty getting to the Logbook &amp;amp; Stamp. Just find the key. Be as Stealthy as possible, even on the Main Street sidewalk. HaHaHa! There is plenty of SWAG for all ages, so swap out if you want. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;img alt="yes" height="23" src="https://cdn.ckeditor.com/4.22.1/full-all/plugins/smiley/images/thumbs_up.png" title="yes" width="23" /&gt; Congratulations to &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ShawnSoter&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; for FTF!!! &lt;img alt="yes" height="23" src="https://cdn.ckeditor.com/4.22.1/full-all/plugins/smiley/images/thumbs_up.png" title="yes" width="23" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e74c3c;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;Remember, the Logbook &amp;amp; Stamp are to remain in the container when you are done.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the South Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b19ba586-1a55-44b3-8eb2-0781c0a8e99a.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Retired Guy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Just open the Trapdoor</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363457798"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T07:41:09</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2426415">BeachBumsX2</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Another Odyssey cache collected on my trip. No trackables in the cache at the moment. 

Day 13/14 Goodbye GWSXXII in Hutchinson, Kansas on Day 12 and hello long days on the road back to Florida. TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364608179"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-20T06:59:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="35451479">naturelvr59</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Sweetbeamie and I, along with our Geopup Little Bear are headed to GeoWoodstock 2026! Our second GeoWoodstock. 
 We spent May 17th to May 24th traveling from our home in Elkhart Indiana through OH, KY, TN, NC, SC, GA, FL, LA, MS, AR, MO, KS, NE, IA, IL. 
 So many goals checked off and so many cool caches along the way. Thanks to every geocacher that puts out and maintains caches for us all to enjoy in our adventures across this great country.   TFTC
 Sweetbeamie beat me to figuring it out. 😑 </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361872025"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-17T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5141535">sirkdizzzle</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">My hotel was 'only' half hour away so had to stop here after a long day off driving. Nice creative setup here!

Spending the week on the road pursuing oldies, virtuals and other cool stops along the way from New Orleans to Kansas for Geowoodstock XXII weekend with the homies. 

Thanks to SirDrumalot for placing this Letterbox Hybrid for me to find!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361365625"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-16T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3251646">JB10-4</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Second cache odyssey for us. Love it 

Day 2 of Team JBB’s giant GeoWoodstock 2026 adventure is officially underway!
After an overnight stay at Buc-ee’s, we got ourselves rolling this morning and pointed the cache-mobile toward another day full of smileys, miles, and adventure. Today’s plan includes working on some fun targets like Cache Odyssey Louisiana, Cache Odyssey Mississippi, Bonita Lakes, Wild Azaleas Cache, and whatever other interesting stops happen to jump out at us along the way.
That’s one of the best parts of a trip like this. Sure, we have a destination, but the real fun is in all the little side quests between here and Kansas. A quick cache here, a cool stop there, maybe a “this should only take five minutes” that definitely does not take five minutes… and somehow it all becomes part of the story.
We’re continuing west, adding more finds to the trip, and enjoying the ride one cache at a time.
GeoWoodstock 2026, we’re getting closer!
Thanks for the cache!
Team JBB — JB10-4 &amp; Blue Thunder 15


Thank you SirDrumalot for hiding "Cache Odyssey - Mississippi" to be find 3309 for us.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361365888"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-16T08:26:51</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="53461557">BlueThunder15</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks for the cache found with JB10-4</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="41.13945" lon="-104.818"><time>2024-12-30T00:00:00</time><name>GCB0CG6</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - WYOMING by lasouthpaw</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB0CG6</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - WYOMING</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9759645" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - WYOMING</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>lasouthpaw</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="5479446">lasouthpaw</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="47" inc="1">Field puzzle</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="1">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Wyoming</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/81da709c-264b-4f44-9ec4-01116521d8bb.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;"&gt;Welcome to Cache Odyssey Wyoming located at the Wyoming State Museum.  Permission for this geocache has been granted by the director of the museum.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;"&gt;The final container for this cache is located INSIDE the building.  The museum is open Mon-Sat from 9:00 to 4:30, except state and federal holidays.  For the most up to date information about the museum&amp;#39;s hours, click here to go to the  &lt;a href="https://wyomuseum.wyo.gov/"&gt;Wyoming State Museum Website&lt;/a&gt;.   Admission to the museum and its programs is free.  You can parallel park on the streets close to the museum and there is a small parking lot north of the building.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;"&gt;This cache is a letterbox hybrid and contains a stamp.  &lt;u&gt;The stamp is NOT a trade item/swag, please leave it in the cache!&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;"&gt;When you are at the posted coordinates, you will see a large cowboy boot.  Locate the blue license plate from 1962 and enter the 5 digits from that license plate into the certitude checker (do not include the 62).  The completion message will tell you where to start your adventure and how to proceed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.certitudes.org/certitude?wp=GCB0CG6"&gt;&lt;img src="https://www.certitudes.org/logo?wp=GCB0CG6" title="Click to see the list of solvers" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;div style="font-family:Comic Sans MS;"&gt;You can validate your puzzle solution with &lt;a href="https://www.certitudes.org/certitude?wp=GCB0CG6"&gt;certitude&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#2980b9;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;Don&amp;#39;t forget to complete the Adventure Lab stops while inside the museum!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/dc1ef0d3-cc02-4bea-a708-6638ef80c69e.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

