&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Northwest Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b19ba586-1a55-44b3-8eb2-0781c0a8e99a.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;RetiredGuy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>One of these things is not like the other.  Give the lower right corner a little tug...</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364411118"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T11:19:31</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2909634">JL_HSTRE</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Stopped here on my journey. I enjoyed exploring the museum exhibits, though I had trouble with the low lighting. Some of the exhibits are also being changed out for a 250th exhibit opening in a month.

The last clue gave me trouble because I misunderstood what it depicted. It has not been affected at all by the exhibit changes. The front desk attendant kindly pointed out what I had overlooked.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364249594"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T15:26:36</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="345266">oneNonly</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We had a hard time locating the cache because they are in the process of moving and changing exhibits.  We did another walk through and finally figured it out on our own.  This is our first cache odyssey!  Tftc </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364038051"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T09:27:57</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4208218">raven45</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Very nice museum. Well designed geo tour. And the final hiding spot made me say wow!
Thank you to the CO and to the museum for hosting the cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363963951"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3400914">backroads2010</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I am on an extended solo road trip from Tucson, Arizona. My first goal was Geo Woodstock in Kansas last Saturday. Then I went over and got the oldest geocache in Missouri and now I'm headed back West. I need to be in Quincy for a 50-year forestry summer camp reunion this Saturday. So I'm blasting through states and counties and geocaches and cool sites. I wanted to see more of the city of Cheyenne so I spent some time getting geocaches here and wandering around. 

I was very interested in getting this. I missed out on an opportunity in another city because it was a Sunday or a holiday, I can't remember, so it wasn't available. I figured out the first part and had it inside. And then it felt like I was completely lost. I looked very suspicious so I spoke to the gentleman at the front desk and he was a little bit helpful but not much. I finally got the hang of what was going on and found the final stage in spite of different exhibits being closed. I figured out where I thought the container would be and work done. Trying to access it, but I couldn't and I certainly didn't want to break anything in a museum. So I headed back to the front desk and spoke to the gentleman again. He did not know anything about it to help me. And like I said, I did not want to break anything in a museum! He pointed out another person who I went over and spoke to and the man laughed and told me not to worry and explained exactly how the mechanism worked so I was right on track. I just hadn't tried hard enough. Headed back, got it open, signed the log and headed on out! Looks like a cool museum. I just didn't have a lot of time to spend there today. Today. You. Favorite point.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364102695"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T09:41:42</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="36292886">pammy24VT</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Great museum loved all the amazing history. Enjoyed walking around exploring. Smashed some Pennie’s and took lots of photos. 
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="43.495917" lon="-96.680633"><time>2024-11-23T00:00:00</time><name>GCB0MN6</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - South Dakota by SoDakZak</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB0MN6</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - South Dakota</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9767488" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - South Dakota</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>SoDakZak</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="13143252">SoDakZak</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="53" inc="1">Park and grab</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="52" inc="0">Night cache</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="1">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>South Dakota</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>**PLEASE NOTE FOR SEPTEMBER-DECEMBER 2025 THIS CACHE WILL BE AT THE POSTED COORDINATES OFF TREETOP AND BAHNSON STREETS… NOT AT THE LIBRARY. I’LL DELETE THIS TOP WHEN THE CACHE IS REPLACED AND BACK AT THE LIBRARY**

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/658927b0-9a5b-4e7d-866f-3f28bcfc6995.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Welcome to South Dakota’s part of the GeoTour!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Final can be found by adding .006 to the North and Subtracting .006 from the West&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please keep the stamp in this Letterbox cache! Please also note the business hours of this library: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;9am opening every day except Sunday. Closing time varies between 5pm (Sat/Sun) 6pm (Wed/Fri) and 8pm (Mon/Tue/Thur)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Midwest Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b19ba586-1a55-44b3-8eb2-0781c0a8e99a.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;RetiredGuy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;






</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Ask one of the kind librarians at the front desk for assistance.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364909743"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T18:38:22</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="637986">Wollaston</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">See logs below.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364909677"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T18:31:53</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="637986">Wollaston</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Well this is a very odd Cache Odyssey. Literally found the container 2’ from the curb laying on the grass? Sorry to say it’s the most uninteresting Odyssey cache I’ve done so far. I’ve placed the container behind the green power box as it’s the only potential cover near by. Day 21 visiting from Downunder 🇦🇺, outnabout on a little hunting adventure after another awesome GeoWoodstock. It’s always a great day for caching. 😎
TFTC SoDakZak

If you’ve been to a GeoWoodstock you’re already checking out next years event. If not, check out GCBNWDV GeoWoodstock 2027 in Baton Rouge, Louisiana. May 29, 2027 and log a will attend to do your bit in achieving GIGA status. It’s a bucket list event that never disappoints.

Log my GW Ambassador trackable:  AM1889.   🙂</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364751064"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T19:03:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3067478">JavaJudt</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Woo hoo, South Dakota's Cache Odyssey!! Of course with a little extra driving - I accidentally navigated to the parking coordinates (library) instead of the cache's temporary location. 🤦‍♂️ Made it there in the end!    
    
Spending the day in Sioux Falls to have lunch, find caches, and who knows what else. TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364496234"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3381039">geofishing-stpc</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Glad this one is still active, but hope it gets back to where it belongs.

We are working on the Odyssey cache series, this is our 32nd. Other Odyssey caches found: North Dakota, Minnesota, Kansas, Missouri, New Jersey, Delaware, Maryland, Pennsylvania, Connecticut, Rhode Island, New Hampshire, Vermont, Maine, Massachusetts, Florida, Oregon, California, Arizona, Oklahoma, Arkansas, Georgia, Tennessee, Kentucky, Indiana, Illinois, Iowa, Nebraska, Wyoming, Idaho, Nevada, and Washington.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364405643"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T11:58:04</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Needs Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1149235">Nurse 1</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Very confusing information and CO is not responding to inquiries. Needs to be disabled or archived. It is behind an electrical box in a neighborhood. Lot by it looks like construction is soon occurring with big mounds of dirt. Very frustrating!

Thanks

Nurse 1</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="41.5212" lon="-90.57245"><time>2024-11-09T00:00:00</time><name>GCB06ZW</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Iowa by Burnt Turtles &amp; GeoTribeFive</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB06ZW</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Iowa</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9754334" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Iowa</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Burnt Turtles &amp; GeoTribeFive</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="14097309">Burnt Turtles</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Iowa</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/658927b0-9a5b-4e7d-866f-3f28bcfc6995.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1 style="text-align:center;"&gt;Welcome to Iowa!&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e74c3c;"&gt;This Letterbox Hybrid is &lt;strong&gt;at &lt;/strong&gt;the posted coordinates. Please &lt;strong&gt;do not &lt;/strong&gt;remove the stamp or logbook. There is no need to bend, twist or force anything in order to find this cache. Please be respectful during your visit.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1 style="text-align:center;"&gt; &lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;h2 style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:medium;"&gt;With permission granted by Matt Magers this cache is located indoors &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2 style="text-align:center;"&gt;Available during the following times&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;Monday 10AM-6PM&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;Tuesday 10AM-6PM&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;Wednesday 10AM-6PM&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;Thursday 10AM-6PM&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;Friday 10AM-6PM&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;Saturday 10AM-4PM&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;*Sunday Closed*&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;(hours may differ during holidays - plan accordingly)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;With over 3 million active GCs around the &lt;u&gt;world&lt;/u&gt; some of the most popular hides are right here in the United States. From Davenport, IA you have the unique option to choose a direction and go. Mingo is an 11hr drive West, Gilby is an 11hr drive North, Eternal Flame Falls is an 11hr drive East and if you wish to visit Infernal Device 2.0, you guessed it...11hrs South&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;But hey, while you&amp;#39;re here, please enjoy your stay. The Midwest Region is happy to have you! &lt;br /&gt;
For more information click &lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/geocaching/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTEAAR30wHZEmrj5vPzQhhoBgqgRwQQyaxcm-C_9RvvVUAtZ0Q4ji-Y2vPfgBig_aem_pBCLog39v3TSKspw8xk2SA"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;Congratulations to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;mafiamastiffs2 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;on FTF!!! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Midwest Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b19ba586-1a55-44b3-8eb2-0781c0a8e99a.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Retired Guy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364381998"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4239635">Jeph_Gileadite</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Came to Davenport this morning to do this Cache Odyssey cache and the Webcam. I wondered around the store a bit looking for the container which was just me being dumb, I probably saw the container a few seconds after I walked in, I just didn't recognize it as the container. Thanks to this business for hosting this Cache Odyssey cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364068428"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T13:28:01</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5743657">loveair</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Fantastic place. Bought a Birthday gift for my Grandson can’t wait to get home and have fun with him with it. Thank you clever!!! With CMA8 </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364071309"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="79259">BlackstoneVal</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">On a caching Odyssey road trip around the Midwest to Geowoodstock and any other stops that catch our interest.  On the way back home to Central Massachusetts we stopped in Davenport and found the major Art Hobby shop open, so in addition to the primary mission, we found a collectible item to take with us.  Gets a fave for Mississippi.
Val and Mar from New England with CMA8</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364066363"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="135681">Scout338</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">From Central MA. Happy to be in Kansas for GeoWoodstock. Mingo was on our bucket list. We are heading back to MA doing Odyssey caches and states. Cool container! A little bit of shopping too!  Took a TB to move along. Thanks for the fun. 
Scout338[:D]</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364065964"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="553797">~Marvalus</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Giving a favorite point! Great little shop! TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="30.27385" lon="-89.78265"><time>2024-11-08T00:00:00</time><name>GCB05R5</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Louisiana by Leather and Lace</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB05R5</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Louisiana</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9753165" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Louisiana</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Leather and Lace</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="381740">Leather and Lace</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="59" inc="1">Food nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="62" inc="1">Seasonal access</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Louisiana</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/078c6545-c107-4d96-b1de-870b357c26ad.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="color:#2980b9;"&gt;The Key: On the visible spectrum the color is found in the range between 445 and 500&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="color:#2980b9;"&gt;The Mailbox: The degrees in a circle will open with the Key&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="color:#2980b9;"&gt;Congratulations to Robert04 with the FTF!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Olde Towne Soda Shop&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Soda History&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This building began its operation in 1930 as the Giordano shoe store. Mr. Nunzio Giordano sold and repaired shoes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Frank Jackson refurbished the building and opened the Olde Towne Soda shop in 1988. He and his family turned the Soda Shop into an iconic location in Olde Towne Slidell. After Hurricane Katrina the Soda Shop was closed for Seven Years but the community asked him to reopen and he did. He retired in 2020. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The new Owners Joshua Roques and Angela Morant Roques took over and reopened after the restrictions of Covid ended in September 2020. They excitedly allowed this cache to be set up in this location. Angela stated &amp;quot;I support any activity that encourages children to get outside&amp;quot; Brandie, the manager also is knowledgeable about Geocaching. She told me that she was making maps for a Governmental agency when Geocaching started! How Cool!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patio is where the accessible entrance is and an easy find for this cache!!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the South Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3" style="text-decoration:none;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#1155cc;"&gt;&lt;u&gt;https://coord.info/GT4F3&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1" style="text-decoration:none;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#1155cc;"&gt;&lt;u&gt;https://coord.info/GT4F1&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4" style="text-decoration:none;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#1155cc;"&gt;&lt;u&gt;https://coord.info/GT4F4&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0" style="text-decoration:none;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#1155cc;"&gt;&lt;u&gt;https://coord.info/GT4F0&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2" style="text-decoration:none;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#1155cc;"&gt;&lt;u&gt;https://coord.info/GT4F2&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF" style="text-decoration:none;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#1155cc;"&gt;&lt;u&gt;https://coord.info/GT4EF&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/9513b58f-0611-4f7b-8598-f5b685afca75.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Retired Guy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364355970"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T08:48:38</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1025025">sfcchaz</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Dropping TBs. 

I did not see the ones that were currently listed in the cache. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362356794"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-20T14:27:02</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="25980352">Jacey516</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Love the Soda shop. Thanks for the hide. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362304827"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-20T09:51:11</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6041752">Winston4Ever</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I’m caching with Lil Devil to GeoWoodstock in Kansas. We flew into Pensacola yesterday. Today, we started in Mobile Alabama. This cache was on our target list. It was cool! Thanks Leather and Lace for the fun! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362304794"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-20T09:51:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="12409">Lil Devil</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Greetings from California. Winston4ever and I are caching our way from Florida to Kansas for GeoWoodstock. Having a great time. Today we started in Mobile, AL and we are hoping to get to Monroe, LA. We're stopping for challenge caches, high favorite points, counties, and anything else that strikes our fancy.     
    
Cool location. Unfortunately they weren't open yet so we couldn't get ice cream.  Thanks to Leather and Lace for the fun. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364606964"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-20T08:56:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="35451479">naturelvr59</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Sweetbeamie and I, along with our Geopup Little Bear are headed to GeoWoodstock 2026! Our second GeoWoodstock. 
 We spent May 17th to May 24th traveling from our home in Elkhart Indiana through OH, KY, TN, NC, SC, GA, FL, LA, MS, AR, MO, KS, NE, IA, IL. 
 So many goals checked off and so many cool caches along the way. Thanks to every geocacher that puts out and maintains caches for us all to enjoy in our adventures across this great country.   TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="42.212667" lon="-89.206833"><time>2024-09-22T00:00:00</time><name>GCAYB0X</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Illinois by halemeister</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCAYB0X</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Illinois</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9698628" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Illinois</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>halemeister</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="2284758">halemeister</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="52" inc="0">Night cache</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Illinois</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/ca87c6ff-e691-4737-b5ca-aaae1d57933b.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span dir="auto"&gt;The posted coords bring you a large sign that has two large brown posts. You will use this sign to figure out the numbers needed for the combination lock that&amp;#39;s on the container, which is located inside the nature center.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;

Use the &lt;b&gt;four big words&lt;/b&gt; on the sign to get the lock combo. &lt;br /&gt;- The amount of letters in the first word is the first digit on the lock combo. &lt;br /&gt;- The amount of letters in the second word is the second digit on the lock combo... and so on.&lt;br /&gt;- After you're done counting you will end up with four digits.&lt;br /&gt;- Go inside the nature center (hours of operation are listed below) and find the ammo can. &lt;i&gt;(hint: it's under the guest book registry)&lt;/i&gt;. Either one of the red doors will get you there, and both are handicapped accessible. 
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span dir="auto"&gt;The nature center&amp;#39;s hours are:&lt;br /&gt;
Monday - Saturday 8am-4:30pm&lt;br /&gt;
Sundays and Major Holidays - CLOSED&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PLEASE DO NOT REMOVE THE SPECIAL "CACHE ODYSSEY - ILLINOIS" STAMP FROM THE CACHE!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the &lt;b&gt;East Central Region Geotour&lt;/b&gt;. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour - &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;https://coord.info/GT4F3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour - &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;https://coord.info/GT4F1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour - &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;https://coord.info/GT4F4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour - &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;https://coord.info/GT4F0&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour - &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;https://coord.info/GT4F2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour - &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;https://coord.info/GT4EF&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/9513b58f-0611-4f7b-8598-f5b685afca75.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Retired Guy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1365027296"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T14:28:32</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="13932513">Caraline7</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nice area for a cache! Loved this one!! Staff was very friendly! Thank you :))</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364991829"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="16271950">grandmabonnie44</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Beautiful setting for the cache. Stopped in while traveling back to Wisconsin from  Pennsylvania.  TFTC.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364991591"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T10:51:53</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="468159">cjhanson</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This is our last cache for our road trip. Got the number code for the padlock. Found the cache in good shape but only 1 trackable in it. Not sure I will ever finish the series but it was a fun find.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364417733"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T12:48:31</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4239635">Jeph_Gileadite</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Quick find here. Friendly staff here. This is my 20th Cache Odyssey cache. I checked out the hiking trails after finding the cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364241309"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T15:24:49</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2670525">saintvi</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">MaxB and I are on the last stage of our journey home to Michigan from GeoWoodstock, via Kansas, Nebraska, Iowa, South Dakota, North Dakota, Minnesota, Wisconsin, Illinois and Indiana. This was the final geocaches on our list, and the 7th Cache Odyssey we found on this journey, including the one in Missouri we found on the way to Kansas. This was such a peaceful place! Thank you for bringing us here, and tftc.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="44.78745" lon="-93.6018666666667"><time>2024-12-23T00:00:00</time><name>GCB0WZE</name><desc>Cache Odyssey- Minnesota  by geocachingvlogger and bflentje</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB0WZE</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey- Minnesota </urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9774502" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey- Minnesota </groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>geocachingvlogger and bflentje</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1661907">geocachingvlogger</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="47" inc="1">Field puzzle</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Minnesota</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/658927b0-9a5b-4e7d-866f-3f28bcfc6995.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;Welcome to Minnesota&amp;#39;s Cache Odyssey Geocache! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a 3 stage letterbox geocache.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This geocache can only be found during the following hours:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, and Thursday from 10 am to 8 pm&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Friday from 10 am to 5 pm&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Saturday from 10 am to 3 pm&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At the posted coordinates you will find a physical geocache &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;placed outside&lt;/u&gt; with facility permission&lt;/strong&gt;, and inside it, you will be able to unlock info for the next stage with your smartphone.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Once you find the final cache &lt;u&gt;DO NOT remove the stamp from the cache. &lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Good Luck! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A VERY BIG THANK YOU TO bflentje for helping me create this amazing geocache! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Midwest Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b19ba586-1a55-44b3-8eb2-0781c0a8e99a.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;RetiredGuy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Stage 1: On the outside of the building across from the library. Hide-a-key under meter. 
Stage 2: The Loon is winking at Dewey.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364109096"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2670525">saintvi</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">MaxB and I are taking the scenic route home to Michigan from GeoWoodstock by way of Gilby ND. On the way to Kansas and the way back we've picked up six Cache Odyssey caches, with one more to find tomorrow. This one has been the most enjoyable so far. Thank you for a fun stop on a long day in the car.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363957097"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T19:13:36</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="620351">SEBURR</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Needed a hint, the staff was very helpful. Tnln tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364495800"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3381039">geofishing-stpc</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">On this Geocaching trip, our goal is to get Minnesota, North Dakota, and South Dakota Odyssey caches. We are also going to spend a coupe of days in Gilby. 

This is our 30th Odyssey cache. Other Odyssey caches found: Kansas, Missouri, New Jersey, Delaware, Maryland, Pennsylvania, Connecticut, Rhode Island, New Hampshire, Vermont, Maine, Massachusetts, Florida, Oregon, California, Arizona, Oklahoma, Arkansas, Georgia, Tennessee, Kentucky, Indiana, Illinois, Iowa, Nebraska, Wyoming, Idaho, Nevada, and Washington.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362519035"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-21T14:44:26</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6853910">fishincacher</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Neat find on our travels thru the area.  Enjoyed finding this one. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362518793"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-21T14:42:12</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1790295">i.findit</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Finally got an opportunity to grab a Cache Odyssey cache.  We were passing thru and decided to stop.  Thanks for the fun cache.  I’m a huge fan of libraries and this one didn’t disappoint.  </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="32.978083" lon="-86.354633"><time>2024-12-27T00:00:00</time><name>GCB0CFV</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Alabama by WhiskeySowers</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB0CFV</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Alabama</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9759634" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Alabama</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>WhiskeySowers</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="15562295">WhiskeySowers</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="2" inc="1">Access/parking fee</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="55" inc="1">Short hike (&lt;1 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="47" inc="1">Field puzzle</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="31" inc="1">Camping nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Alabama</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/078c6545-c107-4d96-b1de-870b357c26ad.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Location:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;Flagg Mountain is the southernmost Appalachian peak over 1,000 feet, located near Weogufka, Alabama, in Coosa County, and contains a CCC-built lookout tower and shelters. Weogufka State Forest consists of 240 acres of upland hardwood on Flagg Mountain. It is owned by the State of Alabama and Managed by the Alabama Forestry Commission.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;The property is open to the public. &lt;u&gt;Visitors are expected to purchase a $5 day pass to visit the state forest. A pass can be purchased in advance (at website below), or on site using a QR code found on a kiosk at the parking lot.&lt;/u&gt; Weogufka State Forest contains many hiking trails maintained by the Alabama Forestry Commission. The Pinhoti Trail’s southern terminus ends on Flagg Mountain. (The Pinhoti Trail extends northward to Springer Mountain in Georgia, where the Appalachian Trail begins.)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;The cache is accessible anytime, but the tower is only open Thursday through Monday, 9am to 6pm. The current forestry worker has worked hard to ensure visitors have a great scenic view from the site, whether or not visitors are able to/choose to go to the top of the tower.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;Special thanks to fellow cachers Trycacheus and SmokinRiverRat for donating materials for this hide! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;Video found on FB: (a bit of a spoiler about what the drive to/from and tower looks like, but not about the cache) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.facebook.com/reel/1627945445193742"&gt;Gage Go Ham - Flagg Mountain Tower&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;History of area:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;The property was acquired mainly from Kaul Lumber Company in the 1930s to build a new state park. After the depression, the federal government created the CCC Program to provide jobs to help rebuild America. Built by the CCC in 1935, the 50’ stone tower is a unique structure. The walls are 2 to 3’ thick. Large timbers were laid in the rock in a crisscross pattern and have been replaced with inlaid stone. Additionally, ten shelters were built on the mountain by the CCC crew (with only five still existing today). Flagg Mountain Lookout Tower is listed on the National Historic Tower Site as tower #250.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;Additional information about Weogufka State Forest: &lt;a href="https://www.forestry.alabama.gov/Pages/Management/WeogufkaSF.aspx" style="color:#467886;text-decoration:underline;"&gt;https://www.forestry.alabama.gov/Pages/Management/WeogufkaSF.aspx&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note on accessibility: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;There is a 1/2 mile fully accessible ADA compliant trail that leads from a gravel parking lot (referred to as the &amp;quot;Lower Lot&amp;quot;) to the top of the mountain and the observation tower. The trail itself is a 60-inch-wide poured cement trail with a gentle slope and many, many switchbacks to get you to the top of the mountain, leading through the forest. The parking lot is gravel, but has designated handicap parking. The road that leads to the trail is passable, but very bumpy and not suitable for very low clearance vehicles. There is an &amp;quot;Upper Lot&amp;quot;, but the gate to get to that lot is not always open and there is no designated handicap parking in the Upper Lot.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Of other interest: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;The first survey marker was placed on Flagg Mountain in 1889. The marker was a “beer bottle, sunk into the soft micaceous shale, which underlies the soil, until its mouth was two feet underground.” At one point, a 1.5-inch drill hole was drilled into the floor of the lookout room on top of the tower that would allow the tower to be used as a triangulation station. In 1930, a “standard bronze disc was set in the old drill hole which marked the station.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;The CCC company that built the tower was Company 260, hailing from Upper New York, New York City, and New Jersey. The company’s slogan was “We can take it.” (“It” being the isolation of the remote forest and agricultural region that he company men were unaccustomed to and the hardship of the work.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;The word “Weogufka”, means “muddy water” is a combination of the Maskoke (also spelled Muskogee) word “wi” (water) and “ogufki” (muddy). The nearby town of Weogufka was settled in 1836 by a migration of 40 Cherokee and mixed White-Indian families, led there by Thomas Ridge from the mountains of Tennessee. They fled to remote Coosa County and changed their names to avoid the infamous “March of Tears” to Oklahoma. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;While visiting Flagg Mountain you may hear the sound of drums. The sound would be coming from the organization Ekynv Yefolecvlke, which is a Maskoke collective that became the official land owners of 577 acres in January of 2018. The ecovillage consists of Maskoke persons whose families ended up in Florida, Oklahoma, and south Alabama. The mission is for collective members to heal in their ancestral homelands and holistically be Maskoke People in a linguistically and culturally grounded Maskoke world.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;**Congrats to Leather and Lace for FTF!**&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the South Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;East Central Region GeoTour GT4F3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour GT4F1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour GT4F4&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour GT4F0&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour GT4F2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#0782c1;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour GT4EF&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/9513b58f-0611-4f7b-8598-f5b685afca75.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Retired Guy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Step 1: Grab magnetic container from alongside the box and remove field puzzle to open.
- 1st word minus 10
- 2nd word minus 8
- 3rd word minus 11

Step 2: Retrieve items from the top before removing inner container. Solve field puzzle.

</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363555362"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3251646">JB10-4</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Our favorite odessey so far. 
Day 11 of Team JBB’s GeoWoodstock 2026 road trip is here — the final stretch!
We’re leaving Starkville, Mississippi this morning after grabbing the webcam, and now we’re pointing the cache-mobile toward Alabama. Today’s plan is to hit Cache Odyssey Alabama, grab one more webcam, and then finally make the last push home.
It’s hard to believe this giant adventure is wrapping up. We’ve gone from Florida to Louisiana, Mississippi, Texas, Oklahoma, Kansas, Arkansas, Alabama, and plenty of places in between. We’ve chased old caches, virtuals, webcams, Adventure Labs, events, a GPS Maze, the GeoWoodstock mega, roadside oddities, salt mines, and more “just one more cache” moments than we can count.
Now it’s time to bring the trip home, with a few final smileys to close it out properly. What a ride this has been!
Thanks for the cache!
Team JBB — JB10-4 &amp; Blue Thunder 15

Thank you WhiskeySowers for hiding "Cache Odyssey - Alabama" to be find 4158 for us.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362733963"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-22T17:08:26</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="56569">xrayrepairdude</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">On a road trip around the SE. states to do some sightseeing, find States Oldest caches, Cache Odyssey caches, getting counties as needed as we pass through and a long list of other interesting caches all while having a grand adventure as we go!

TFTC, made the very treacherous drive from the N to the lower parking. OH.MY.GOODNESS!!! It’s been raining for a couple days, so that “road” was a mess…and narrow…and slick clay! 😳😱 Thankful we have 4WD as 4L was handy and reassuring. Once we got to the lower parking it was a relatively easy walk to the top. Of course we were here on a Friday and upper lot is open Thur &amp; Sat. 😜 We made quick work of both puzzles and were able to get in to sign the log. The final GZ location is really cool and Mrs X climbed to the top of the tower, but getting to Flagg Mountain was quite the adventure! This is our 15th Cache Odyssey. FP awarded. 

Thank you WhiskeySowers for the Letterbox Hybrid cache. This is number 9678 for us. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362225332"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-19T17:33:50</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="35451479">naturelvr59</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This is heck of a drive back here. The last section of road is only open Thursday and Saturday 9-6pm. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360775552"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-13T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2426415">BeachBumsX2</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">My 2nd Odyssey cache but not my last on this 14 day trip.
I like a challenge and it gave me just that. 
Great spot and view too!
Stopped to grab another Alabama cache before heading to all the north states that I need before GWSXXII. TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1355645043"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-17T17:02:12</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="54855425">heatherrosee</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This is hard but fun! I did all the work 😭</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="41.428667" lon="-86.89825"><time>2024-12-16T00:00:00</time><name>GCAZNR5</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Indiana by TeamPhoenix421</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCAZNR5</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Indiana</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9738750" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Indiana</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>TeamPhoenix421</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="6473620">TeamPhoenix421</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="59" inc="1">Food nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="58" inc="1">Fuel nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Indiana</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/ca87c6ff-e691-4737-b5ca-aaae1d57933b.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 style="font-style:italic;text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:24px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to Wanatah, Indiana, host of Indiana&amp;#39;s Cache Odyssey GeoTour stop. Indiana is the &amp;quot;Crossroads of America&amp;quot;, dubbed in 1937 due to several major highways intersecting through Indiana&amp;#39;s state borders; several of which span coast to coast.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:22px;"&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:#f1c40f;"&gt;THE CACHE IS NOT AT THE POSTED COORDS!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:#f1c40f;"&gt;But, you need to navigate there to start!!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:#f1c40f;"&gt;The coordinates provided will bring you to a depository embedded in the north wall of the library. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:#f1c40f;"&gt;Using the Certitude Checker below, enter the first word on the face plate to obtain final instructions to make this find.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:#2ecc71;"&gt;Please note that the Stamp is not a trade Item and MUST remain with the cache. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;LIBRARY HOURS&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mon. 11:00am - 6:00pm&lt;br /&gt;
Tues. 9:00am - 6:00pm&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wed. 11:00am - 6:00pm&lt;br /&gt;
Thurs. 11:00am - 5:00pm&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fri. 11:00am - 5:00pm&lt;br /&gt;
Sat. 9:00am - 1:00pm&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sun Closed.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(Holidays may differ)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.certitudes.org/certitude?wp=W1AZNR5"&gt;&lt;img src="https://www.certitudes.org/logo?wp=W1AZNR5" title="Click to see the list of solvers" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;div style="font-family:Comic Sans MS;"&gt;You can validate your puzzle solution with &lt;a href="https://www.certitudes.org/certitude?wp=W1AZNR5"&gt;certitude&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the East Central Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b19ba586-1a55-44b3-8eb2-0781c0a8e99a.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Retired Guy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364876105"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T13:59:14</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5951003">Chi-Town Smurf &amp; AJ</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This is a quaint, quiet, little town. The cache, of course, is what  brought us here. Our discoveries were plentiful. Exceptional set up and a great way to educate new cachers. Craftsmanship is stellar. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364875240"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T13:54:50</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4076193">Chque_Norris</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found it today with Chitown Smurf </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364855987"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T12:19:14</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4239635">Jeph_Gileadite</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I was here when the doors opened. I met two other cachers here from Wisconsin. Talked to an employee who hopes to take up Geocaching when he retires.  I was going to leave a Travel Bug, but I didn't think it was safe here. I got my passport stamped and off I went.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364844094"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="16271950">grandmabonnie44</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Just my second Cache Odyssey find. Don't know that I will ever visit all of them as that would require return to many states.  TFTC.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364845571"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T11:26:54</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="468159">cjhanson</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">My 6th Cache Odyssey. Always enjoy these quality geocaches. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="34.994133" lon="-84.945433"><time>2024-12-13T00:00:00</time><name>GCAZJD1</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Tennessee by Super_Nate &amp; Chattanooga Area Geocachers</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCAZJD1</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Tennessee</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9735522" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Tennessee</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Super_Nate &amp; Chattanooga Area Geocachers</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="222374">Super_Nate</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="47" inc="1">Field puzzle</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="52" inc="0">Night cache</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="14" inc="0">Recommended at night</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="46" inc="1">Trucks/RVs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="58" inc="0">Fuel nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="31" inc="0">Camping nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="60" inc="1">Wireless beacon</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Tennessee</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/ca87c6ff-e691-4737-b5ca-aaae1d57933b.png" width="500px" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;"&gt;Cache Odyssey - Tennessee is an engaging geocaching experience located in the picturesque &lt;strong&gt;Red Clay State Historic Park&lt;/strong&gt; in Bradley County. Known for its rich Cherokee history and natural beauty, the park provides the perfect backdrop for this unique and educational, fully accessible letterbox hybrid.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLAN AHEAD!&lt;br /&gt;
THIS GEOCACHE IS ONLY AVAILABLE WHEN THE PARK IS OPEN *:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jan - Feb: &lt;/strong&gt;8am - 5pm&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Mar:&lt;/strong&gt; 8am - 6pm&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Apr:&lt;/strong&gt; 8am - 7pm&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;May - Aug:&lt;/strong&gt; 8am - 8pm&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Sep:&lt;/strong&gt; 8am - 7pm&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Oct:&lt;/strong&gt; 8am - 6pm&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Nov - Dec:&lt;/strong&gt; 8am - 5pm&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;7 days per week&lt;br /&gt;
*Hours are listed in eastern time zone.&lt;br /&gt;
Visit &lt;a href="https://tnstateparks.com/parks/red-clay"&gt;Red Clay State Historic Park&lt;/a&gt; website to verify current hours.&lt;br /&gt;
Admission is free!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;"&gt;This is a gadget cache of sorts, with two codes to crack before the letterbox vault will fully unlock. The coordinates posted are for the cache. To access the log, the experience begins before getting out of your vehicle. Simply pull into a parking space, and tune into &amp;#39;Cache Odyssey Radio,&amp;#39; broadcasting live from the Red Clay studios on &lt;strong&gt;92.5 FM&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;"&gt;Every single day, Ranger Ridley can be heard on air, broadcasting historical tidbits about the significance of the Cherokee at Red Clay. During his segment, he shares some important symbolic numbers needed to unlock the letterbox vault. It&amp;#39;s important to note these numbers in the following order:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="margin-left:40px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1. Council Grounds&lt;br /&gt;
2. Blue Hole Spring&lt;br /&gt;
3. Eternal Flame&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;"&gt;Once the code is cracked, a large case is revealed and can be retrieved. You must then solve one more puzzle to access the log.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Inside is a log book, quality swag, and 2 letterbox stamps. One of the stamps is for the Cache Odyssey passport, the second is unique to Tennessee, which can be used on personal letterbox log books.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In addition to signing and dating the physical log, please write where you&amp;#39;re visiting from, how many Cache Odyssey&amp;#39;s you have visited, and include a sentence or two about your experience at Cache Odyssey - Tennessee.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;"&gt;If you enjoyed your visit, please consider giving this cache a favorite point. If you see the park rangers out and about, especially Logan, Erin, and Taylor, tell them hello and thank them for supporting quality geocaching at Red Clay State Historic Park.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/a4288518-f4ba-47c4-b44a-22c693b3b60d.jpg" /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey GeoTour Kickoff event  &lt;/strong&gt;|&lt;strong&gt;  December 30, 2024&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Media coverage: &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;a href="https://www.timesfreepress.com/news/2024/dec/30/red-clay-state-park-in-cleveland-tenn-part-of/"&gt;Red Clay State Park in Cleveland, Tenn., part of national Cache Odyssey project making Geocaching wheelchair accessible&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;em&gt;Chattanooga Times Free Press&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.clevelandbanner.com/news/national-cache-odyssey-kicks-off-locally-at-red-clay/article_1fd190dd-04ef-5a4e-bdf1-9368925ed434.html"&gt;National Cache Odyssey kicks off locally at Red Clay&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;em&gt;Cleveland Daily Banner&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.podcacher.com/show-894-0-geocaching-small-world-stories/"&gt;Show 894.0: Geocaching Small World Stories&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;em&gt;Podcacher Podcast&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" style="width:80%;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the East Central Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/76de9cdc-8b3c-4816-8280-2fbc61852b60.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/18d9b309-a90c-4900-a735-2eedd7912009.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/0f404634-c476-4cd5-b8df-f85d6aa8069e.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/dc93f2f7-97ae-4cb4-a9e1-8986f081414f.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/179e8963-86e3-49a1-bc17-fd28c53b735a.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/f6ab1d02-9794-4521-955f-0bcf19e3c566.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/ba935c3f-3961-459a-a950-8b1462cbe818.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.RetiredGuy.com/CacheOdyssey.html" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;img alt="Cache Odyssey Leaderboard" src="https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/sq2k5rn4e7xgsmqhfd3zc/CacheOdysseyEastCentral.jpg?rlkey=5mgxonnf7x47uopmg17jvp85g&amp;amp;st=i1lc6caz&amp;amp;raw=1" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364172522"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T09:29:05</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1906272">mdsearcher</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Came to Red Clay Park for the Cache Odyssey.  Impressive park.  Will wander around to see more of it.  Cache Odyssey was great fun.  TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364071843"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T14:45:34</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5240023">mimandpap</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">On my way to Knoxville and had to get this one. Had some problem opening the 2nd lock but finally got it. This is my 9th Odyssey Cache. TFTH SL </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363021905"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5268266">Pine Baron</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">5493. Down from New Jersey with the crew visiting family and doing a little caching. This was our first cache this morning and what a way to start the day! This odyssey was amazing from start to finish.

The imagination, ingenuity and craftsmanship here is amazing. Definitely the best of the (6) COs that I've logged and maybe the best overall geocache that I've done. Thanx so much for putting this together for all geocachers to enjoy.

Traded stamps, signed the log and did some bartering. Thanx for all the fun! Definite Blue Ribbon!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362639657"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-22T10:49:33</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="222374">Super_Nate</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Maintenance Check!

Stopped by to reset the radio station. Everything is now working as intended. 

Periodically the station goes down due to power outages. As always, reach out to me if the radio is not working, and I’ll get visitors on the right path. Most of the park staff is aware how to restart the radio, so don’t be shy to ask someone on site as well. 

My goal is for all geocachers to come away with a smiley. I know many folks are visiting from out of state while on road trips. Need help? Just ask!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362549648"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-21T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3797805">mrahudson</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We received massive help from the CO on this one.  At first we didn't know if we were going to be able to get to the log but a very quick reply from the owner got us what we needed.  Favorite point for sure.  4th Cache Odyssey find, only 46 to go!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="44.498517" lon="-87.994283"><time>2024-12-26T00:00:00</time><name>GCB0AHA</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Wisconsin by The Happy Hodag!</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB0AHA</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Wisconsin</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9757758" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Wisconsin</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>The Happy Hodag!</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="202428">The Happy Hodag!</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="59" inc="1">Food nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="26" inc="1">Public transportation nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="58" inc="1">Fuel nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Wisconsin</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/658927b0-9a5b-4e7d-866f-3f28bcfc6995.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;center&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td align="center" width="210"&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;font size="-1"&gt;&lt;font size="-1"&gt;&lt;b&gt;This cache placed by a member of: &lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;a href="http://www.wi-geocaching.com"&gt;&lt;img src="https://drive.google.com/thumbnail?id=19l1AM0lUK-PEFz5o0S6kwYLYSSmheRUQ&amp;amp;sz=s4000" /&gt; &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;font size="-1"&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.wi-geocaching.com"&gt;&lt;font size="-2"&gt;(click to visit our website)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Congrats to tdschmidt on the FTF!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is the Wisconsin edition of the Cache Odyssey series, a series of 50 caches, one in each of the 50 states.  These aren't your average run of the mill every day park and grab caches, these are Letterbox Hybrid caches meant to be genuine terrain 1 caches.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Midwest Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour &lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.geocaching.com/play/geotours/cacheodyssey-eastcentral" target="_blank"&gt;East Central Region&lt;/a&gt;  &lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Cache-Odyssey-East-Central-GeoTour-Passports.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;Passport&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois should be in the Midwest, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.geocaching.com/play/geotours/cacheodyssey-midwest" target="_blank"&gt;Midwest Region&lt;/a&gt;  &lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Cache-Odyssey-Midwest-GeoTour-Passports.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;Passport&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.geocaching.com/play/geotours/cacheodyssey-northeast" target="_blank"&gt;Northeast Region&lt;/a&gt;  &lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Cache-Odyssey-Northeast-GeoTour-Passport.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;Passport&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.geocaching.com/play/geotours/cacheodyssey-northwest" target="_blank"&gt;Northwest Region&lt;/a&gt;  &lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Cache-Odyssey-Northwest-GeoTour-Passport.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;Passport&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.geocaching.com/play/geotours/cacheodyssey-south" target="_blank"&gt;South Region&lt;/a&gt;  &lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Cache-Odyssey-South-GeoTour-Passport.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;Passport&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.geocaching.com/play/geotours/cacheodyssey-southwest" target="_blank"&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/a&gt;  &lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Cache-Odyssey-Southwest-GeoTour-Passport.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;Passport&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/9513b58f-0611-4f7b-8598-f5b685afca75.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Retired Guy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.retiredguy.com/CacheOdyssey.html" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1351136211"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-25T02:01:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="202428">The Happy Hodag!</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I found out recently that one of the places I was considering moving this to has closed down over a month ago.  Maybe it's a good thing that location didn't work out.

 -The Happy Hodag!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1312919021"><groundspeak:date>2025-07-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="202428">The Happy Hodag!</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I just checked, and the new Cache Odyssey cache for Wisconsin published on Wednesday.  Check GCB9GJN

 -The Happy Hodag!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1311257201"><groundspeak:date>2025-07-18T09:05:57</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="202428">The Happy Hodag!</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Screw it, I'll just do it now.

With all the problems I've been having here, between this cache going missing four times in six months, and people expecting me to drop whatever I might be doing so I can run out and maintain this cache, this is over.   I've also been offered help building a new container, but that offer never came through.  I've also asked around at multiple businesses and organizations seeking permission to place this at their location, getting turned down at every single f-ing one.  All while getting hounded by cachers to get it out on their time.  All of this leads me to think that being the owner of this Cache Odyssey cache has taken the joy of being a cache owner out of it for me.  Thanks to all those who came to Green Bay to seek out this cache.  My hope is that the next version of the Wisconsin Cache Odyssey cache will be 100 times better than whatever I could do with it.

 -The Happy Hodag!

P.S.  If Gary is still watching this listing, it's an honor that you even considered me for this.  I still believe that Illinois should have been put into the Midwest region.  I'll be donating $23, $1 for every finder of this cache, to Saint Jude during Podcast of Hope this December, in addition to my normal amound and whatever cash I find in caches between now and then, because #coins4kids ,- it just makes cents.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1311253267"><groundspeak:date>2025-07-18T08:44:33</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="202428">The Happy Hodag!</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">The most recent news about this Cache Odyssey cache can be found on the June 29 episode of Geocache Talk.  Go and find out there if you wish.

 -The Happy Hodag!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1311240910"><groundspeak:date>2025-07-18T07:39:46</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="202428">The Happy Hodag!</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Anyone who is looking for any news, take a listen to the Geocache Talk epiesode from June 29.  That's all I need to say.

 -The Happy Hodag!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="34.169133" lon="-83.562683"><time>2024-10-29T00:00:00</time><name>GCAZQZY</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Georgia by poeanne</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCAZQZY</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Georgia</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9740882" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Georgia</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>poeanne</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="5549208">poeanne</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="47" inc="1">Field puzzle</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="14" inc="0">Recommended at night</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="0">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="51" inc="1">Special tool required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="33" inc="1">Motorcycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="60" inc="1">Wireless beacon</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="62" inc="0">Seasonal access</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="43" inc="1">Livestock nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Georgia</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/078c6545-c107-4d96-b1de-870b357c26ad.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;Welcome to Cache Odyssey - Georgia!  For this chapter of the tour, we have placed the cache at the Jackson County Airport.  The Jackson County Airport sees over 30,000 takeoffs and landings each year, and with your help, it may see a takeoff of one of the most unique objects to fly at the airport!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;Your task is to find the cache which should be the easy part!  Once there, you will have to complete some tasks to find the log and sign.  You will need some specialized equipment to get the job done and be in tune with the cache.  If you drove here, you almost certainly have every single thing you need with you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;Note: please use care when solving this cache!  Nothing should require extreme pulling/pushing or other unnatural acts!  If something seems like it&amp;#39;s not moving, it&amp;#39;s either not meant to move or there may be another way it moves!!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;Remember that the stamp is to use for your passport, but please return the stamp to the cache when you finish.  The stamp is not a trade item.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;Hope you have a &amp;quot;blast&amp;quot; in Jackson County!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" style="width:80%;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the South Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/76de9cdc-8b3c-4816-8280-2fbc61852b60.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/18d9b309-a90c-4900-a735-2eedd7912009.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/0f404634-c476-4cd5-b8df-f85d6aa8069e.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/dc93f2f7-97ae-4cb4-a9e1-8986f081414f.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/179e8963-86e3-49a1-bc17-fd28c53b735a.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/f6ab1d02-9794-4521-955f-0bcf19e3c566.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/ba935c3f-3961-459a-a950-8b1462cbe818.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.RetiredGuy.com/CacheOdyssey.html" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;img alt="Cache Odyssey Leaderboard" src="https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/hm6bipgl0xa4028mlasov/CacheOdysseySouth.jpg?rlkey=omo44cgp0htkxl1zf2iu60qaf&amp;amp;st=vr963f9l&amp;amp;raw=1" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;Cache Odyssey - Georgia&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Park close!  Get power!  Press to extend - release to retract!</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363810825"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T22:50:06</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="30920028">mathmanbill</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Holy moly Batman. That was one of THE best gadget caches I’ve ever done. The time and engineering it took to put this all into place was amazing. It took us a little time to put all the right pieces together but we got there. Bravo!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363695125"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T08:04:04</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3588517">JoeBum</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Wow! That’s easily a top 10 cache. We got up early this morning so that we’d have enough time to stop before our trio around Lake Lanier. I’m so glad we did. Awesome idea and really well put together. Thanks for all the work that must have gone into this. Definitely sets the bar for best Cache Odyssey really early…</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363357671"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5268266">Pine Baron</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">5517. Down from New Jersey with the One More Cache Crew visiting family and doing a little caching. We took an hour drive to finish up our day with this recommended cache. Since we're from New Jersey and really wanted log it, I reached out to the CO to make sure we had the proper TOTT. She graciously replied and aided us.

We found what we needed to help us proceed. Very, very cool! But alas, our TOTT was not functioning! Panic set in as we tried everything we could but couldn't figure it out. Panic turned to dismay when Piglet404 yelled, "It's working!". We all gathered around and GeoJ0sh was smart enough to record the code.

He did the honors and we were soon trading stamps, signing the logbook and bartering swag. This was an awesome, custom-built geocache with an excellent puzzle attached. Thanx for the gamut of emotions, from awe, to sadness, to elation! I could easily give this 2 favorite points, but you'll have to settle for one. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362945112"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T14:44:13</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="22414030">clammybird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nice easy find found quickly like the spot and placement nobody around very quiet out with CJ4fish and Wolflover0 WOW that's all the best odyssey cache by far awesome loved it thanks for bringing me here and the smiley 🙂 signed in got out TFTC </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362906161"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T12:31:24</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11181996">DTCharlie</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">OK, that was pretty awesome. I saw the pictures, I read the description, I even looked at the hint, not exactly what I was expecting. Love all the thought and production that went into this geocache. Of course it is getting a favorite point. I have gotten quite a few of the odyssey geocache’s now. And this one definitely ranks up as one of the top. Thank you to the CO and everyone who put work into this so that people like me can have a lot of fun.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="34.8637" lon="-111.810717"><time>2024-11-01T00:00:00</time><name>GCAZX8D</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Arizona by AhernClan</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCAZX8D</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Arizona</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9744989" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Arizona</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>AhernClan</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="4432325">AhernClan</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="55" inc="0">Short hike (&lt;1 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="47" inc="1">Field puzzle</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="51" inc="1">Special tool required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="59" inc="1">Food nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="46" inc="0">Trucks/RVs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="58" inc="1">Fuel nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Arizona</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b7be9a3d-4cd6-45a8-a96e-a3a45b233f37.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e74c3c;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:22px;"&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:#ffff33;"&gt;Please do not take the stamp! These are part of the letterbox cache. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e74c3c;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:22px;"&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:#ffff33;"&gt;Please do not park &lt;/span&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:#ffff33;"&gt;ANYWHERE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:#ffff33;"&gt; near the Fire Station bays.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e74c3c;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:22px;"&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:#ffff33;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:#ffff33;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:24px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Comic Sans MS,cursive;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e74c3c;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:#ffff33;"&gt;This is a VERY ACTIVE fire station !!!!!! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:#ffff33;"&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;                                             &lt;span style="font-size:24px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Comic Sans MS,cursive;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e74c3c;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;👩‍🚒👨‍🚒🚒🚑👨‍🚒👨🏽‍🚒🚒🚑👩‍🚒👨🏽‍🚒🚒🚑&lt;/u&gt;. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;This is Arizona&amp;#39;s Southwest Regional letterbox hybrid cache for the Cache Odyssey Project. Whether you choose to go for more regional Cache Odyssey finds or not, the main thing is to have fun! There is a gadget (field puzzle) portion to this cache, so be patient and use your noodle! A special but common TOTT is provided (spare included). Nobody should walk away with a DNF! And please replace everything as found for the next adventurer!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;Cache is placed on government property with the permission of Sedona Fire Chief Ed Mezulas. Although night time is still accessible, remember Sedona&amp;#39;s Bravest may be sleeping 😴! (So if you must go at night, do so quietly please 😁- otherwise we may lose our location). Thank you to the SFD for being a part of the geocaching community! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;And remember, &lt;u&gt;please leave the stamp&lt;/u&gt; for the next finder so they can stamp their passport!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;NOTE: I&amp;#39;ve left a folding chair behind the cache since it low to the ground. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#2980b9;"&gt;Congrats to GravyTrain54, DaCacheMonkeys and ShadowOfMingus on shared FTF!!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Southwest Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b19ba586-1a55-44b3-8eb2-0781c0a8e99a.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Retired Guy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>1. Outer lock - in plain sight.
2. Inside lock - instruction sheet located inside. Use TOTT (provided or if missing, you will need a 9V battery)
3. How do you climb a ladder?</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1365014927"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T11:16:17</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="391008">dcdawn</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Visiting from Wisconsin. Today I was headed from Flagstaff to Buckeye AZ via Sedona and Phoenix. I had a full agenda of geocaches, checking out a favorite eatery (part of a western chain that doesn’t exist within 900 miles of my home), and hopefully meeting up with geo-friends M&amp;D.

I was needlessly worried about earning a smilie for this gadget letterbox cache. I totally enjoyed myself, though, especially as I had a comfortable place to sit while I attempted to rescue Fluffy. It took a while, but I’m pleased to report Fluffy is safe and I have my smilie. Thanks for a super creative and fun hide.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364873263"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5431034">sth2878</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Visiting from Washington State, but actually staying in my vacation home in Surprise for a week. We have friends staying with us and we wanted to get out and explore Sedona while in AZ. 

We found a wonderful VRBO in Uptown and used that as our landing pad while sightseeing, hiking, shopping, eating, and (for me) geocaching our way around this beautiful city. 

After hiking Fay Canyon, I requested a stop at the fire station on our way back to Uptown. My muggle friends and wife happily obliged. We found parking across the street and my wife and I meandered over to the obvious cache. 

I grabbed the chair and got to work. First step was guessed correctly on my first try. Upon opening the front door of the station I immediately knew what I had to do. But finding the sweet spot took a good 10 minutes. I excitedly signed the log and celebrated this find by swapping 3 trackables.  

There are so many reason this deserves a favorite point:
•I’m a firefighter, so this location. DUH!
•The size of the cache alone. 
•You provide a chair for comfort.
•It’s a gadget cache that works perfectly !

TFTH today, a day that I needed a large and letterbox!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364266373"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="21350310">carda1</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Teamed up with DaSeadogs and, between the two of us, we were able to figure out all the steps. Very well done. Definite fave point. Thank you so much for putting this together. 
With DaSeadogs on a 18 day adventure picking up states, counties, challenges, high favorites and oldies. From Wisconsin</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364264314"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="21667841">DaSeadogs</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">How fun we teamed up and got it done. I took care of one part and carda1 took care of the other. Thank you so much for bringing us to this beautiful location and the Odyssey Stamp. thanks for the folding chair - It came in handy favorite point for sure. With carda1. Bravo Zulu - FP+1.
Go Navy.
SL RAF TFTC
"May the finds be with you"</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362207000"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-19T13:05:49</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="40810470">MuadDib256k</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Tftc! The chair was a nice, appreciated touch!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="42.956367" lon="-85.48765"><time>2024-12-23T00:00:00</time><name>GCB02X4</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Michigan by Merlin1392</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB02X4</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Michigan</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9750405" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Michigan</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Merlin1392</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="928860">Merlin1392</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="47" inc="1">Field puzzle</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="51" inc="1">Special tool required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="64" inc="0">Tree climbing required</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Michigan</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/09a471ed-679f-4b98-8d7c-f1092aae0f45.png" style="height:212px;width:750px;" /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/c7636bd1-428c-48e4-a17c-6e617326a622.png" style="height:494px;width:750px;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;Signal was visiting the area and wanted to do some lite reading.  So he stopped at this wonderful library in Ada, Michigan.  While here he couldn&amp;#39;t help himself and left a geocache for you to find.  The posted coordinates take you to the front door of the Amy Van Andel Library.  A library within the Kent District Library System.  Unfortunately, you can only access the geocache during &amp;quot;normal business hours&amp;quot;.  However, there are many days and times available.  Please see the KDL website (&lt;a href="https://kdl.org/locations/ada/"&gt;https://kdl.org/locations/ada/&lt;/a&gt;) for the most current.  &lt;strong&gt;NOTE: as of 6/1/26&lt;/strong&gt;, the hours were:&lt;br /&gt;
Monday     9:30am - 8:00pm&lt;br /&gt;
Tuesday     9:30am - 5:00pm&lt;br /&gt;
Wednesday     9:30am - 5:00pm&lt;br /&gt;
Thursday     12:00pm - 8:00pm&lt;br /&gt;
Friday     9:30am - 5:00pm&lt;br /&gt;
Saturday     9:30am - 1:30pm&lt;br /&gt;
Sunday     Closed&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;Now, once you arrive at the library, during hours of operation, enter the front door.  There is a lovely courtyard in front of you that offers a very quiet place to get some sunshine and read a book.  However, the cache is not there.  Continue to the left and arrive at the circulation desk.  There, the friendly, cheerful and helpful librarians can fill you in on all of the wonder to behold in the library.  After passing the desk, turn to your right.  Follow this hallway to a point near the elevators.  Feel free to check out the second floor, but I think you&amp;#39;ll be able to spot the object of your affection before you get to the elevator.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;Please note:  This cache does require cash to access!  Not much, only &amp;quot;two bits&amp;quot;.  Once you gain access to the cache location look near the top, you will find a large white tube.  To the left is an opening and your &amp;quot;two bits&amp;quot; should be returned.  During testing, it worked 99% of the time!  However, if your coin is not returned do not despair.  The cache will be checked regularly, and any coins not returned to their rightful owner will be donated to a very worthy charity. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Double note:  This is a publicly available cache.  As such, I believe that folks from the public that do not know our game, open the container and remove SWAG.  This includes trackables as well.  I have filled the bucket three times with SWAG which is getting expensive.  I know geocachers will &amp;quot;trade&amp;quot;, but pretty sure the public will not.  Enjoy the experience, but I do not recommend dropping off trackables any longer.  Sorry to say.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&lt;/strong&gt;  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/177a3105-afb9-42a5-b70b-9373b72ce101.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="color:#27ae60;"&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey!&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Cache Odyssey&lt;/em&gt; is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt; geocache to &lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What&amp;#39;s the Mission Behind Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;This isn&amp;#39;t your average cache series! We’re here to prove that &lt;strong&gt;geocaching&lt;/strong&gt; is a game for everyone—no matter your physical abilities or location. &lt;em&gt;Cache Odyssey&lt;/em&gt; aims to show that &lt;strong&gt;Terrain 1&lt;/strong&gt; caches can be just as daring and innovative as the most challenging hides. Because after all, not every adventure needs to be a D5T5!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Makes Cache Odyssey Special?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;When you embark on a &lt;em&gt;Cache Odyssey&lt;/em&gt; adventure, you can expect:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wheelchair-accessible caches&lt;/strong&gt;: Every hide is designed for ease of access.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Letterbox hybrids&lt;/strong&gt;: Each cache combines the thrill of geocaching with the creativity of letterboxing.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Regular or larger containers&lt;/strong&gt;: No micro hides here—get ready for some substantial, satisfying finds!&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Unmatched creativity&lt;/strong&gt;: Prepare for some of the most innovative, high-quality caches out there. Each one is designed to surprise and delight!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the East Central Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Start Your Cache Odyssey Adventure!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;Ready to hit the road? Whether you&amp;#39;re a seasoned geocacher or a curious newcomer, there&amp;#39;s an adventure waiting for you in every state. Begin your journey today and see just how fun, accessible, and creative geocaching can be.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;Happy caching, and remember—&lt;strong&gt;the journey is the destination!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&lt;/strong&gt;  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.RetiredGuy.com/CacheOdyssey.html" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;img alt="Cache Odyssey Leaderboard" src="https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/k5o6me915ukqsjjg1pqnf/CacheOdyssey.jpg?rlkey=2rrlouaaoh9g52pjieu8e5ohj&amp;amp;st=kgtptrow&amp;amp;raw=1" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1365028905"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T15:44:27</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4779775">cohutta seekers</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Slowly working through the states.
Beautiful library and nice cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364906641"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T18:46:37</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="55543618">willybilly4545</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364905623"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T18:30:51</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4239635">Jeph_Gileadite</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I had no problem with the mechanism. And it even gave me my cash back! Thanks to the Kent District Library for hosting.  Loving this Cache Odyssey series.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364384866"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T11:27:18</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="51221941">brikrambo</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">another one down we love doing these </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364099665"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T17:47:53</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5548736">triforce66</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">What a fun cache! Everything is in good working condition. Added some swag. #9 for our cache odyssey tour. Tftc </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="40.161167" lon="-111.575683"><time>2024-11-15T00:00:00</time><name>GCB0D8Y</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Utah by Jokeerus</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB0D8Y</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Utah</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9760381" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Utah</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Jokeerus</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="3332037">jokeerus</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="53" inc="0">Park and grab</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="52" inc="0">Night cache</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="14" inc="0">Recommended at night</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="1">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Utah</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b7be9a3d-4cd6-45a8-a96e-a3a45b233f37.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#c0392b;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:#ffffff;"&gt;Due to vandalism and theft, this cache isn&amp;#39;t in the greatest of shape. I have received the new stamp to replace the old one, but because of the situation, I don&amp;#39;t dare leave it in the cache until a better lock is in place. I do have a couple of options for you in stamping your passport.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#c0392b;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:#ffffff;"&gt;A- I have the stamp in my front yard cache GC9DWQ0 Cozy Cottage which is only a couple of minutes away and you could stamp your passport there.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#c0392b;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:#ffffff;"&gt;B- You could message me your address and I will mail you a stamped label sticker you could put on your passport.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#c0392b;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:#ffffff;"&gt;There will be a temporary log replacement added to the Cache Odyssey later today. If you visit before then, please either send me a picture of you with the container or leave a piece of paper inside of it with your geocaching name.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#c0392b;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:#ffffff;"&gt;I am terribly sorry for this inconvenience and hope you can have an enjoyable adventure in finding this cache.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#c0392b;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:#ffffff;"&gt;NOTE: The container is currently laying on its side and more difficult to discover. When you get to the final &amp;quot;area,&amp;quot; think of yourself as standing at 6 o&amp;#39;clock and walk toward 8 o&amp;#39;clock and you should see it laying down &amp;quot;over the edge.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/72f66943-b5fb-4a4e-bdbf-917305402ee8.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/423ba16a-290d-4711-b12c-0e1a783d50d1.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/2652cf02-1258-49cd-8573-47d351d63404.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/c50fd92f-02c4-4d86-82be-1ec9cd77e63d.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/2f107719-2b48-45df-ace1-9f15f42665ab.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.certitudes.org/certitude?wp=W1B0D8Y"&gt;&lt;img src="https://www.certitudes.org/logo?wp=W1B0D8Y" title="Click to see the list of solvers" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;div style="font-family:Comic Sans MS;"&gt;You can validate your puzzle solution with &lt;a href="https://www.certitudes.org/certitude?wp=W1B0D8Y"&gt;certitude&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;
