&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/e079b01b-b5ce-4c02-bc95-b54b3b81dec3.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16.0pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:white;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:&amp;amp;quot;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:black;"&gt;Links: &lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Cache-Odyssey-Southwest-GeoTour-Passport.pdf" style="color:#0563c1;text-decoration:underline;"&gt;SW Passport  &lt;/a&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16.0pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:white;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:&amp;amp;quot;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:black;"&gt;  &lt;a href="geocaching.com/play/geotours/cacheodyssey-southwest" style="color:#0563c1;text-decoration:underline;"&gt;Southwest GeoTour &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16.0pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:white;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:&amp;amp;quot;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:black;"&gt;  Info on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16.0pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:white;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:&amp;amp;quot;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:black;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/geocaching/" style="color:#0563c1;text-decoration:underline;"&gt;All Cache Odyssey Geotours&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Southwest Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b19ba586-1a55-44b3-8eb2-0781c0a8e99a.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;RetiredGuy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>See note at the very top of the cache page.
Solve the lock code, enter it into Certitude and you will be shown some picture clues for your journey.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364106362"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T17:37:40</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="9460917">MamaBugg</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found without intending to find a cache here. Just enjoying a walk and there it was.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362316717"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-20T09:55:41</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="362398">GameForTravel</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found It - quite an adventure!

Thanks!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361869038"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-17T18:41:32</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8614773">Zargonians</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We got our stamp for the Cache Odyssey from the CO's travel bug hotel at their home.  Hope this one can be revived soon.  Thanks for being a party of the Cache Odyssey!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360069349"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-09T16:10:22</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="609455">Data Wrangler</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I made this one harder than it was. I misinterpret one of the clues and was hunting in the wrong place. Fortunately, a quick message to the CO got me back on track. On a pre-GWXXII trip from Florida. SL, TFTC.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1356130543"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-03T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6452459">coppertopjen</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">"MR ODYSEEY AND HIS GRAND ADVENTURE" wanted to visit and get picture taken with this specific cache 


</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="48.146017" lon="-97.469233"><time>2024-12-25T00:00:00</time><name>GCB0AM3</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - North Dakota by Trycacheus</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB0AM3</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - North Dakota</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9757844" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - North Dakota</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Trycacheus</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1628741">Trycacheus</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="65" inc="1">Yard (private residence)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="47" inc="1">Field puzzle</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="64" inc="0">Tree climbing required</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>North Dakota</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! 
 

 



&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/658927b0-9a5b-4e7d-866f-3f28bcfc6995.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Welcome to Johnstown, ND where the subject of the "Pull my Finger" cache lives and my wife grew up.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Today you will be helping them out and having fun getting a geocache also. Finding this cache needs no force, everything should reveal itself by simply turning a couple of knobs. Start with the red knob after opening up the top box. Please be sure to close up all the doors (3) before leaving. Be aware that my father-in-law may approach you, he is mostly harmless, but do not pull his finger. &lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Midwest Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b19ba586-1a55-44b3-8eb2-0781c0a8e99a.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;RetiredGuy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;






</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Start by dumping the garbage.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364756731"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T20:46:32</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="887579">dukemartin</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found it with Paintedwarrior.  That was fun.  Took two travel bugs to move them east.

Thanks for the cache. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364616885"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T09:26:07</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1454863">Paintedwarrior</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Enjoyed our visit to the sanitation station. No garbage was found, just a fun cache. Thanks for putting together such an awesome cache. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364464166"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T16:10:23</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5660998">janjorjack</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">That’s pretty cool.  I dropped a TB.  Thanks for the smile.  </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364489080"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T16:06:54</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="22496111">StonesFanInTO</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">2026 WTF Group Roadtrip of Manitoba; North Dakota &amp; Minnesota.

Day 3:  Grand Forks, ND

Spending our first full day in Gilby working on geo-tour; assorted gadget caches; challenges and whatever else we pass by.

Almost all Gilby gadget caches probably all deserved favourites.  Unfortunately I have a very limited supply available of favourites.

Nice setup.  Always happy to get a cache in this series.

Signed/stamped all caches WTF

TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364495023"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="47235">capjap</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Road trip with WTF. An ambitious list of caches to find. But we are up to the task!  I always like these kinds of caches. TFTC </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="33.57755" lon="-81.799333"><time>2024-11-07T00:00:00</time><name>GCB04VT</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - South Carolina by MPDrayer</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB04VT</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - South Carolina</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9752286" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - South Carolina</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>MPDrayer</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="23729908">MPDrayer</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="47" inc="1">Field puzzle</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>South Carolina</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/078c6545-c107-4d96-b1de-870b357c26ad.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt; &lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;To open the &lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;blue&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;birdhouse&lt;/span&gt;, solve the following riddle.  Look carefully!  The letters underlined in &lt;span style="color:#c0392b;"&gt;red&lt;/span&gt; form a word:&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;I wander around, but I don&amp;#39;t have a clue,&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;I don’t search for treasures like the cachers do.&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;I’m not in the know, not part of the crew,&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;I&amp;#39;m just a &lt;img height="57" src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/4ca68790-e3a7-41b0-8f3f-4a6bb862bce5.jpg" width="164" /&gt;, passing through.&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt; &lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt; &lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;When you&amp;#39;re in the woods and feeling lost,&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;A friendly guide comes at no cost.&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;He’s green and hopping, ready to log,&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;He’s your friend, &lt;img height="51" src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/12179811-9700-44a2-b5a8-f3bc98555649.jpg" width="367" /&gt;.&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt; &lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt; &lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;If you want the cache, but don’t want the fun,&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;You can find the clues before you&amp;#39;re done.&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;But be warned, these hints may ruin the game,&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;They’re called &lt;img height="53" src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/662e514c-7e0e-4f63-800e-897e55f67868.jpg" width="196" /&gt;, and they’re often to blame.&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt; &lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
You’ve found the cache, but don’t be done,&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Sign your name before you run.&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;It’s small and handy, you’ll need it again,&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;To leave your mark, you’ll need a &lt;img height="51" src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/e4ce7f21-b2ef-475c-919b-8cbb39eb4d3b.jpg" width="65" /&gt;.&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;Note:  Letterbox Hybrids contain both a logbook and a stamp.  The exclusive South Carolina Cache Odyssey stamp is not a trade item and should stay in the cache.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;Gregg Park Civic Center is open during these times:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;Monday – Thursday:  8:30 AM – 9:00 PM&lt;br /&gt;
Friday:  8:30 AM – 8:00 PM&lt;br /&gt;
Saturday:  8:30 AM – 7:00 PM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

