</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Pro tips:
If the gadget won't turn on, unplug it and then plug it back in.
If the gadget is not displaying correctly, hold it at the base to prevent it from wobbling.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363583529"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T15:09:37</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="30920028">mathmanbill</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">OCW JoeBum on day 3 of 4 of our caching roadtrip based around ATL. After trudging through the jungle to get Modoc last evening, we opted to stay in Aiken afterwards and picked up a few caches here before heading up to Charlotte and then Clemson. 

Now that was a fun, well thought out, creative cache!  Fav point! TFTC. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363535770"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T12:41:40</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3588517">JoeBum</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Day 3 of an oldie roadtrip with mathmanbill. This was one of our targets for today. This one was a cache that kept on surprising us. Lots of levels to discover. Thanks for the creative and fun cache</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362909237"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T12:43:36</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11761201">jennifercoleman21</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">So fun!! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362909066"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T12:43:13</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8316255">nason.crystal</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Amazing!!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362847038"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T09:11:25</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11181996">DTCharlie</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">OK, let me start by saying I was not going to give this geocache a favorite point. First of all my first here was on a Sunday. I did read the hours for the Civic Center, but because it did not specifically say the geocache was not available, I thought it would be on the outside And still attainable. Of course I was mistaken. Second, on my second trip here, which is today, due to all the rain there was a tiniest bit of warping of the wood, which made the latch very hard to open, and I banged my knuckles because of it. Third, after all that it was like, I have to walk all the way over there with all the stuff just to figure this out?
OK, all of that being said, it definitely gets a favorite point. This geocache is difficult when you first look at it, but it becomes so simple when you just think for a minute. So I love how it is so simple and difficult at the same time. And oh my gosh was it fun. So yes, it is definitely getting a favorite point.
Thank you to the CO for creating this fun.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="39.5489" lon="-79.980133"><time>2024-11-30T00:00:00</time><name>GCAY6NR</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - West Virginia by Troopbiz</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCAY6NR</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - West Virginia</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9694470" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - West Virginia</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Troopbiz</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="2464712">Troopbiz</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="53" inc="0">Park and grab</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="47" inc="1">Field puzzle</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="66" inc="0">Teamwork cache</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="64" inc="0">Tree climbing required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="10" inc="0">Difficult climb</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="54" inc="0">Abandoned structure</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="17" inc="0">Poisonous plants</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>West Virginia</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/ca87c6ff-e691-4737-b5ca-aaae1d57933b.png" style="width:500px;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Welcome to wild and wonderful, West Virginia! Birthed during the Civil War and forged from the coal mining industry. the Mountain State is the 35th state to join the Union. Being the most southern of the northern states and the most northern of the southern states, West Virginia is unique thanks to its rich cultural history and hospitable charm. Combine this with the unique topography of the region, and it&amp;#39;s easy to see why this area is called Almost Heaven.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This cache in your tour of America will bring you to the heart of Appalachia, Camp Muffly. Located just off Interstate 79 between Fairmont and Morgantown, this park is home to 4-H camps, festivals, weddings, and the casual summer picnic. Please be mindful of activities happening at the park during your visit, especially during the summer months, but they shouldn&amp;#39;t negatively impact your search.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You are searching for a large crate-like container with a lock &lt;em&gt;(it shouldn&amp;#39;t be hard to spot)&lt;/em&gt; on the porch of the park office. To open the cache and sign the log, you&amp;#39;ll need to enter the year West Virginia joined the union into the lock. This year is significant because West Virginia is the only state formed as a result of the Civil War. Please enjoy the assortment of SWAG in this large container and replace everything exactly as you found it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I hope you enjoy this special project and seek out some of the other caches in this series!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" style="width:500px;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

