	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Georgia,serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;History&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Georgia,serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;This cache is located in the Freehold Public Library at &lt;span style="background-color:#f8f9fa;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#202122;"&gt;28&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;sup&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:#f8f9fa;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#202122;"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:#f8f9fa;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#202122;"&gt;⁄&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;sub&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:#f8f9fa;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#202122;"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:#f8f9fa;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#202122;"&gt; East Main Street&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. One of the last few of 36 Carnegie libraries in New Jersey that is still used as a public library.  The build was recently renovated to be ADA compliant and with central air-conditioning installed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Georgia,serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;It replaced the &lt;span style="background-color:white;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#202122;"&gt;original Freehold library that opened on January 6, 1900, in the Lloyd Building at the corner of West Main and Throckmorton Street with a collection of 500 volumes but was destroyed by fire in December 1901&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. After the fire Marion Laird, chairwoman of the Library Committee of the King&amp;#39;s Daughters, wrote to Carnegie asking for financial support for a new library building. The philanthropist offered $10,000. Freehold was the ninth town to get a grant from Carnegie, and the second town to complete their new building.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Georgia,serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:white;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#202122;"&gt;In the spring of 1903, The King&amp;#39;s Daughters raised $2,000 through donations to buy the lot from the widow Doty. In the summer of 1903 Frederick A. Brower contracted to construct the new library, which cost of $8,874 and opened the following year.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Georgia,serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:white;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#202122;"&gt;The Monmouth Inquirer wrote about the news of the new library on July 30, 1903.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Georgia,serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:white;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#202122;"&gt;“Plans for the Carnegie Library building at Freehold have been prepared … The new library will be 44 feet front and 55 feet deep and will be built of brick.  The front will be very handsome, and a &lt;em&gt;special brick &lt;/em&gt;will be used ... There will be a six foot stoop and the structure will contain a main floor with a 16-foot ceiling, a basement with 10-foot ceiling and an attic&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Northeast Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b19ba586-1a55-44b3-8eb2-0781c0a8e99a.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;RetiredGuy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Look Down, lower right.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364686818"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="372678">tallglenn</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Passing through on our way to GWXXII, we missed the Cache Odyssey TX because it was closed Sunday. We missed Cache Odyssey OK because it was closed Monday. On the way home from GWXXII, we missed Cache Odyssey KS because it was closed Sunday. Looking forward, I hope Cache Odyssey owners will have mercy on the travelers from afar and place them in 7 day/week locations.  </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359731731"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-08T09:01:04</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="21194">nikcap</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">The Library is still closed, and I haven’t confirmed the integrity of both stages. This will happen as soon as the library is reopened.  
If you have question please message me. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1358351841"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2654798">loves to fish</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nothing wrong with the cache container...saw on news that there was a shooting there, Library said they will be open next Monday.  Hoping it gets enabled soon for everyone</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1358131734"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-30T18:26:24</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="21194">nikcap</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Need to check on the container. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1358135004"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5613572">JerseyEric</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Uh, why are there police with rifles standing in front of this library???  What the heck is inside your cache container?

I was about to pass the library at 7pm on my way home from Philly.  Thought about stopping to do this cache or at least look at the 1st stage.  Not happening!    The police have secured the area!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="41.45685" lon="-72.8169"><time>2024-12-29T00:00:00</time><name>GCB0AVG</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Connecticut by Firefighter Skippy</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB0AVG</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Connecticut</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9758043" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Connecticut</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Firefighter Skippy</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="336027">Firefighter Skippy</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="1">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Connecticut</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;Welcome to Wallingford CT and the Wallingford Public Library. You will be looking for some information at the posted coordinates that will lead you  to the geocahche. Since this is a letterbox hybrid you will find a stamp inside along with a logbook. The stamp is NOT swag and should be left inside the container. It is available during  normal business hours - Mon-Fri: 9:30am-9:00pm, Sat: 9:30am-5:00pm, Sun: Closed. Thanks to Library director Sunnie Scarpa and her staff in setting up and hosting this geocache.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey - Connecticut !&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Northeast Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b19ba586-1a55-44b3-8eb2-0781c0a8e99a.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;RetiredGuy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Numbers on a sign.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364268127"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:20:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3794567">rabbitgeocacher</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This cache was my main goal of the day. Road-tripped over from RI to make the find. Very nice library and cache! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363736499"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="247532">kkcjrlma</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">A fun stop on our way south to visit RL. Left a trackable. Tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363347141"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T20:35:27</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="55478433">HannahG111706</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">good</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362739896"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-22T19:26:55</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8724011">Candy Apple 68</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Greetings from Letchworth State Park in Mount Morris, NY! :)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363100741"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-22T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5445477">Albus_Birch</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">When planning out this trip, we were thrown a curve ball when we realized the library would be closed on Sat. 5/23 for the weekend of Memorial Day.  Altered plans to get Friday night instead.  Driving down the street, saw police lights ahead.  We were concerned, but it turned out to be a traffic incident.  

After parking, we headed up the sidewalk.  Credit goes to my wife for making the find here.  After entering the library, we angled over to the hiding spot and after a brief search, found the cache.  Stamped and returned as found.  

Little did we know that the next morning, we would meet the CO at our meet and greet!  Was nice to chat with him.

8026</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="44.511733" lon="-73.058683"><time>2024-09-15T00:00:00</time><name>GCAY1H8</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Vermont by TKDscouter</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCAY1H8</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Vermont</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9689525" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Vermont</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>TKDscouter</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="920404">TKDscouter</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="47" inc="1">Field puzzle</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Vermont</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/085ef39f-7673-44fc-945f-3579422587dc.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This cache was placed with the permission of the director of the Essex Free Library. &lt;b&gt;To get the answer which will lead you to the cache go to the posted coordinates and count the number of tall black pole lights. Multiply that number by 100.000 then add it to 296.587.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 

&lt;p&gt; &lt;i&gt;&lt;font color="blue"&gt;The library staff do not know the solution but are aware they are hosting the Odyssey Cache. Also, the staff are not responsible for maintenance. Please message me with any concerns.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt; The main entrance is up the steps in the front. ADA access is in the back of the building (follow the sign) and press the buzzer at the door for admittance.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Finally, when you sign and date the log please include the state you are from to help me evaluate the cache popularity and scope. &lt;b&gt;The letterbox stamp must be left in the cache. Do NOT take it home!&lt;/b&gt; Feel free to trade swag and/or drop off trackables.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Library hours are:&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;M, W, F  9am - 5pm&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tu, Th   9am – 8pm&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sat      9am - 2 pm&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sun       Closed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;More information about the library, including holiday closures can be found at &lt;a href="https://essexfreelibrary.org"&gt;Essex Free Library&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Cache-Odyssey-Northeast-GeoTour-Passport.pdf"&gt;Dowload your Cache Odyssey - NorthEast Region GeoTour Passport here.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;Congratulations to 82HammFam on the FTF! Enjoy the Odyssey!!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" style="width:80%;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Northeast Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/76de9cdc-8b3c-4816-8280-2fbc61852b60.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/18d9b309-a90c-4900-a735-2eedd7912009.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/0f404634-c476-4cd5-b8df-f85d6aa8069e.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/dc93f2f7-97ae-4cb4-a9e1-8986f081414f.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/179e8963-86e3-49a1-bc17-fd28c53b735a.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/f6ab1d02-9794-4521-955f-0bcf19e3c566.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/ba935c3f-3961-459a-a950-8b1462cbe818.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.RetiredGuy.com/CacheOdyssey.html" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;img alt="Cache Odyssey Leaderboard" src="https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/ya3m72utnwkwj8fst4s8i/CacheOdysseyNortheast.jpg?rlkey=xs3moevmhzuopc77xrt6xygda&amp;amp;st=znlc0dh4&amp;amp;raw=1" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Not Huey or Louie</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363785589"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T16:30:08</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8724011">Candy Apple 68</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Greetings from Letchworth State Park in Mount Morris, NY! :)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363960168"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5445477">Albus_Birch</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">After my wife corrected my count, we had the proper info to find the cache.  

8059</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363121910"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-22T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1369346">roscoe45</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Last one needed to complete the Northeast.  Very nicely done. Thanks for the Hybrid</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361022005"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-14T22:59:32</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14566146">CheekyBrit</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">By the skin of my teeth I managed to find this one in the last 5 minutes before the library closed. My planning allowed more time for this leg of the journey but the champion cup in Montpelier had traffic ground to a halt for 20 to even 60 minutes in parts. Wild.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359953512"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-09T10:32:15</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3317869">MsGwozdz</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC SL great find while checking off VT towns to celebrate Gary’s birthday (a couple weeks early). All is well here!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="41.7366" lon="-71.56375"><time>2024-11-07T00:00:00</time><name>GCAHEKA</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Rhode Island  by RecipeForDisaster</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCAHEKA</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Rhode Island </urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9344590" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Rhode Island </groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>RecipeForDisaster</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="4741950">RecipeForDisaster</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="65" inc="0">Yard (private residence)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Rhode Island</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/085ef39f-7673-44fc-945f-3579422587dc.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


This cache can only be found during Hope Library's open hours: https://hopelibraryri.org/about. Note that they are closed New Year's Eve 2024, New Year's Day, and January 2nd, 2025. As of December 2024, normal hours were:

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

Monday: 10:00 AM – 5:00 PM &lt;br /&gt;
Tuesday – Thursday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM &lt;br /&gt;
Friday: 10:00 AM – 5:00 PM &lt;br /&gt;
Saturday: 10:00 AM – 2:00 PM&lt;br /&gt;
Sunday: Closed &lt;br /&gt;
If there is a parking ban in Scituate (usually due to winter storms), the library will be closed. Their phone is (401) 821-7910.
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
This would be a great cache to seek during bad weather! There is even free coffee and tea inside (on the right after you enter) as well as wifi. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

You will collect information outside, filling in the blanks at the posted coordinates, and then proceed in to follow clues to the cache once you have your blanks filled in. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; Accessing the information and getting to the cache, including retrieving it, should not be a problem for anyone using a wheelchair. I do not know if the sidewalk around the posted coordinates is plowed if there is lots of snow, though.

Once inside, you will find the standard self-inking Cache Odyssey stamp (in volume I) as well as a hand carved letterbox stamp (in volume II - bring your own ink/markers if you'd like to stamp this one). The volumes are touching each other. Everyone should sign the logbook in volume I - stamping is optional. Because this cache won’t get wet or see animal interaction, you could trade stickers, seeds, and other usually ill-advised items here.&lt;br /&gt;
Thank you to the staff at Hope Library, especially director Cora Morrigan and assistant director Rebekah Hamilton - they were very enthusiastic and helpful! That said, there is no need to interact with any library staff.

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;


Here is how to fill in the blanks (information needed can be found outside at the posted coordinates, below the heavy object made at the local foundry):
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;


Once you have the blanks below filled in, enter the library through the main entrance, and stop in front of the desk. &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;


Take a _____(fourth letter from end of whole north side inscription)______, passing the table and chairs on your left.&lt;br /&gt;
Take a _____(south side, first line, fourth word, third letter)_____, noting the elevator ahead of you. 
&lt;br /&gt;
Take a ____(south side, fourth line, second word from end, fourth letter)______ straight to the wall ahead, checking the ____(# of lines on whole north side)___ shelf up from the bottom for what you seek.&lt;br /&gt;


&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Northeast Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b19ba586-1a55-44b3-8eb2-0781c0a8e99a.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;RetiredGuy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363948644"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T17:48:50</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8724011">Candy Apple 68</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Greetings from Letchworth State Park in Mount Morris, NY! :)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363962211"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5445477">Albus_Birch</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">On Saturday, 5/23, we had collected the necessary info.  Unfortunately, library was closed due to the upcoming Memorial Day holiday (which had not been listed on their calendar).

Drove from Vermont1, oldest Vermont cache, back to here to get this one (after calling to verify it was open).  When we entered, we were greeted warmly with 'have fun!'.  We explained our situation, for which  we were offered apologies and a promise to note on the calendar.

After which, we followed the directions (I love the old school concept) and found the cache in short order.  

Last one needed for our NE Cache Odyssey!

8065</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362287815"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-20T12:57:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8473686">mpark65</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Came out from California to visit my daughter and to watch my granddaughter graduate from high school. Will be here for a month and today I decided to some caching. Thanks to all the CO’s for the smiley and the hide. TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360501095"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-11T18:11:57</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14566146">CheekyBrit</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">That was positively delightful. The instructions had me confused at start but as I put in what I knew I quickly realized I was trying to find twice as many numbers for twice as many blanks as are needed. Thanks for the cache odyssey, it was undeniably lovely.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1357837304"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-28T16:42:37</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="25738294">run26pt2</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Finally got my 900th find  what a incredible journey it’s been   it did take me a minute to figure out the puzzle, but once I finally figured it out and got myself in the right direction I was able to solve it and make the find tftc and here is to another 900 more are to come </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="42.347567" lon="-71.0354"><time>2024-11-07T00:00:00</time><name>GCB04E8</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Massachusetts by RetiredGuy</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB04E8</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Massachusetts</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9751897" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Massachusetts</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>RetiredGuy</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="2758778">RetiredGuy</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="53" inc="1">Park and grab</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="59" inc="1">Food nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Massachusetts</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/085ef39f-7673-44fc-945f-3579422587dc.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;To open the combination lock, come up with the four letter word for what is consumed with pretzels during Oktoberfest.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;It all started with three college buddies and a shared love of beer. Dan Kenary, Rich Doyle, and George Ligeti were passionate about beer, but they weren’t able find what they were looking for on tap at their local pubs. While traveling in Europe after college, they drank many diverse, fresh, local beers and experienced firsthand the wonderful beer culture that existed just across the pond. They wanted to bring that to Boston, so they decided to do just that.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/5f2309e9-b4dd-4f27-ac54-08c46a289b26.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;In 1986 they started the first modern day brewery licensed to manufacture and sell alcohol in Massachusetts and they received Brewing Permit #001 from the Commonwealth.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/1079c309-0383-42b5-b29a-c44765996442.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;In 1992, the brewery introduced New England to India Pale Ales, now ubiquitously referred to as IPAs. The brewery has become known in Boston for annual festivals including Octoberfest (15,000 attendees) and St. Patrick&amp;#39;s Day.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;The employee-owned Harpoon Brewery gave permission to place this geocache on their property and invites geocachers to come find the special geocaching keg that represents Massachusetts for Cache Odyssey! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;"&gt;Please note that while this cache is a terrain 1.0 and has the &amp;quot;available in winter&amp;quot; attribute, should a snow plow clear the parking lot, both of those may temporarily change. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" style="width:80%;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Northeast Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/76de9cdc-8b3c-4816-8280-2fbc61852b60.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/18d9b309-a90c-4900-a735-2eedd7912009.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/0f404634-c476-4cd5-b8df-f85d6aa8069e.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/dc93f2f7-97ae-4cb4-a9e1-8986f081414f.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/179e8963-86e3-49a1-bc17-fd28c53b735a.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/f6ab1d02-9794-4521-955f-0bcf19e3c566.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/ba935c3f-3961-459a-a950-8b1462cbe818.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.RetiredGuy.com/CacheOdyssey.html" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;img alt="Cache Odyssey Leaderboard" src="https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/ya3m72utnwkwj8fst4s8i/CacheOdysseyNortheast.jpg?rlkey=xs3moevmhzuopc77xrt6xygda&amp;amp;st=znlc0dh4&amp;amp;raw=1" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>You should be embarrassed that you asked for a hint. BEER!</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363888540"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1491213">softball29</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Off on a wild day of adventure with JK186 to the Boston area for some caches, the Stamp Expo, lobstah rolls and good weather! Sometimes the mind and body need a day away to be in a good place. What an awesome cache. Well done all around. Fully fits in to its surroundings. I love creativity and workmanship on something like this. Well earned favorite point. Signed and replaced. Thanks for the smiley! 

HooHaa Blog: [My blog about caching and more](http://www.hoohaablog.com/)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363757072"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="17680489">JK186</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found while on another adventure with softball29. On our way to Boston for more fun and exploration. The cache is in good shape,  the log sheet is dry and ready for more signatures. Thank you for creating, placing and bringing us here. Thank you to the CO's, business owners and volunteers that make this happen..Gets a favorite..</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363343850"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5445477">Albus_Birch</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">First place that I chose to park was incorrect, but eventually, we figured out where to park. Must be a fun place when the pickleball courts are in play!

Lock stuck.  Have one just like it and a little WD40 works wonder.  After us both trying it a few times, we got it to open.  

Love the themed hide!  Favorite point!

8041</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363185790"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T10:30:30</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8724011">Candy Apple 68</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Greetings from Letchworth State Park in Mount Morris, NY!  Love the container; FP from me!! :)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362726400"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-22T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="526318">ZSteve</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found this one with HonuHideout today.  We're in the area for a very brief visit and spent the day exploring geocaching style.  It was a beautiful day to be out and I really enjoyed walking around the area and seeing the sights while finding caches.  We didn't have time to find all of the caches that we wanted to during our time here, but maybe we'll get a chance to come back again some time to find some more.  Very nice job on this one.  Things weren't open here during our visit, but it would have been nice to have been able to grab a drink.  It did take some effort to get the lock open, but we finally got it.  Left some bugs for a future finder to move along.  Favorite Point from me.  Thanks for the fun!





</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="43.215183" lon="-70.998133"><time>2024-12-29T00:00:00</time><name>GCAZY1N</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - New Hampshire by substickers</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCAZY1N</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - New Hampshire</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9745741" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - New Hampshire</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>substickers</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="3771387">substickers</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="59" inc="1">Food nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="58" inc="1">Fuel nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>New Hampshire</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:13.5pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to Cache Odyssey - New Hampshire!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This cache has been placed at a special location intended to bring you back to joyful Christmas&amp;#39;s spent every year with family decorating your Christmas tree. It is a Letterbox with the special New Hampshire - Cache Odyssey New Hampshire stamp that can be found nowhere else. You do not need to enter the building to find the cache. Once you find it, you will need the combination to the small lock on the container intended to keep muggles from muggling this hide. Use your own stamp to sign the logbook, or just sign in the normal way. Caching at this location is only permitted during store hours: the store is open daily 10-5. Please be sure to relock the box and spin the combination dial; this will prevent muggles from being able to open the box.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The local men and women in blue will be on the lookout for people prowling around this location at off hours, so please visit only during store hours.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:13.5pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Northeast Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3" style="text-decoration:none;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1" style="text-decoration:none;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4" style="text-decoration:none;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0" style="text-decoration:none;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2" style="text-decoration:none;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF" style="text-decoration:none;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;u&gt; &lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;GeoTour&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;It would be much appreciated if you do not copy and paste the same log for your day of caching. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;As always when Geocaching, have fun, be safe and leave no trace.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Code for lock: 619, viewed on edge of lock</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363594773"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T15:46:48</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8724011">Candy Apple 68</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Greetings from Letchworth State Park in Mount Morris, NY!!  Loved the shopping, too!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363958138"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5445477">Albus_Birch</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Had contacted the store ahead of time to be sure they were open on Memorial Day, which they were.  No one was about as we circled around, before finding the cache, opening, and logging.

As Christmas is my wife's favorite holiday, guess where we went next?

8050</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362899628"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T12:09:33</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="680794">Salmonelas</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC! Found together with Arodama 

We love this kind of caches</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362895909"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T11:57:28</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="37452840">Arodama</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC! Found with Salmonelas. Our second odyssey (after Maine).</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361871685"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-17T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="890383">wwhale</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Me and geodog are heading to the mountains for a mini-stay.  Took a slight detour to find a small pocket of 5 towns I need for the 234 Challenge. I also wanted to add to my Odyssey caches.  Quick find.  Stamped passport and the toured the establishment.  Wow!!! ...the largest Christmas ornament offerings I have ever seen and loved how they were all grouped by theme.  The building wandered foreeever.  I didn"t even go to the second level.  Can't wait to come back when I have more time.  Awesome...dropped a TB and a FTF mini geocoin to move along.   tftAdventure</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="47.580033" lon="-122.135667"><time>2024-11-12T00:00:00</time><name>GCB0AK3</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Washington by Bouncebounce</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB0AK3</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Washington</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9757813" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Washington</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Bouncebounce</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="10794530">Bouncebounce</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="47" inc="1">Field puzzle</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="26" inc="1">Public transportation nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>4</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Washington</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;h1&gt; &lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Tahoma,Geneva,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;This property has surveillance cameras so You may be video recorded when finding this cache. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Tahoma,Geneva,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;If you have previously found some of my archived caches, you might recognize these puzzles. This cache consists of several of my earlier puzzles.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I have been told the LEDs may not all be flashing. The code from the 1st stage should be 395. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;To access the cache tune into radio station 90.5 to get the code to the exterior lock. Use the date given on the radio for the exterior lock code. Once inside start with the appropriate tool and utilize it to decode the flashing lights that will get you into the stage 1 box. Inside stage one use the tool inside to access stage 2. What&amp;#39;s inside stage two you&amp;#39;ll need to arrange the blocks in the quick order to see your four digit code to access stage. Stage 3 you will need to get the correct bidon tube with the log in it. Also, in the stage three box is the stamp for the letter box.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Please make sure to put everything back locations and lock each box. &lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Northwest Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; (Link to Geotour Page)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; (Link to Geotour Page)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; (Link to Geotour Page)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; (Link to Geotour Page)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; (Link to Geotour Page)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;INSERT MAP&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Retired Guy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>If you have any issue with this cache please call or text me 206-372-9680</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1344002464"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-05T14:32:14</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="10794530">Bouncebounce</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Moved to new location, new GC code is GCBGK5Z</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1343998066"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-05T13:28:59</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="226293">Rock Rabbit</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Greetings from Geocaching.com

It looks like your cache has been under the weather for some time. While I feel that Geocaching.com should hold the location for you and block other cachers from entering the area around this cache for a reasonable amount of time, we can't do so forever. Please either repair/replace this cache, or archive it so that someone else can place a cache in the area, and geocachers can once again enjoy visiting this location. Also, if you haven’t done so already, please pick up any remaining cache bits as soon as possible. 

If you reactivate the cache and/or post a note here within a month, then no action will be taken.  Whatever your intentions, please **post a note** here on the cache page (not email) to let us know that you are still active and maintaining the cache.  If a month passes without seeing a response, then I'll assume that this listing should be archived.

Rock Rabbit
Geocaching.com Volunteer Reviewer</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1338482870"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-20T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="20096819">Hamsterius</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Just drove by and saw the building where this cache was is under demolition. So sad.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1333241048"><groundspeak:date>2025-11-05T09:27:47</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="10794530">Bouncebounce</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Will be back up soon</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1332244426"><groundspeak:date>2025-10-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="54122566">Snowythechipmunk</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Tftc! This is my first ever cache. The container is definitely broken, and the logbook seems very finicky. Quite a good find, though!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="43.663317" lon="-124.1982"><time>2024-10-19T00:00:00</time><name>GCAY8C4</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Oregon by emilierene</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCAY8C4</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Oregon</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9696093" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Oregon</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>emilierene</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="505582">emilierene</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="59" inc="1">Food nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Oregon</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/81da709c-264b-4f44-9ec4-01116521d8bb.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Welcome to the Oregon Cache Odyssey geocache. It is a Letterbox Hybrid cache type that pays homage to an older form of a scavenger hunt called Letterboxing. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache contains a signature stamp that stays with the box. Traditionally letterbox seekers have their own signature stamp to make their mark in letterbox logbooks, and they collect letterbox stamps from the boxes they find in their personal book. To seek a letterbox hybrid cache, you will *not* need your own personal stamp or logbook. However, if you have a personal stamp bring it to add to the logbook in this cache. Bring the Cache Odyseey GeoTour passport, your personal logbook, or blank paper to collect a stamp from the signature stamp in this cache. Each stamp in the Cache Odyseey series is unique to its state and the series. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff0000;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;*****THE CACHE ODYSSEY STAMP IN THIS CACHE MUST STAY IN THE CACHE TO PRESERVE THE INTEGRITY OF THIS LETTERBOX HYBRID CACHE******&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div style="--tw-border-spacing-x:0;--tw-border-spacing-y:0;--tw-ring-offset-width:0px;padding:0px;"&gt; &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You can find this cache using only your GPS, but in letterboxing fashion here are a few hints to get the lock combination and then to the hiding spot:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div style="--tw-border-spacing-x:0;--tw-border-spacing-y:0;--tw-ring-offset-width:0px;padding:0px;"&gt; &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At the Umpqua River Lighthouse Museum Gift Shop building &lt;em&gt;take notice of these three things in this order&lt;/em&gt; and use the numbers to unlock the padlock on the cache:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How many round bells are there on the red alarm on the front of the building?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Each of the five dormers has a window. How many panes are in the top arched half of the window?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How many windows are above the double entrance doors?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Spot the outdoor deck.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Explore the deck for a large item that blends in with its surroundings.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Notice the geocaching symbol and lock to confirm you found the cache.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use the three numbers to unlock the cache.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;There could be non-geocachers on the deck, especially in nice weather. You may find it a good opportunity to introduce them to geocaching. No need to worry about them messing with the cache as you&amp;#39;ll be locking it up when you leave.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache has plenty of room for travel bugs and trackables and their hitchhikers. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" style="width:80%;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Northwest Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/76de9cdc-8b3c-4816-8280-2fbc61852b60.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/18d9b309-a90c-4900-a735-2eedd7912009.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/0f404634-c476-4cd5-b8df-f85d6aa8069e.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/dc93f2f7-97ae-4cb4-a9e1-8986f081414f.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/179e8963-86e3-49a1-bc17-fd28c53b735a.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/f6ab1d02-9794-4521-955f-0bcf19e3c566.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/ba935c3f-3961-459a-a950-8b1462cbe818.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.RetiredGuy.com/CacheOdyssey.html" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;img alt="Cache Odyssey Leaderboard" src="https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/ygks8c1e4p0rrvu3wxy1r/CacheOdysseyNorthwest.jpg?rlkey=31rfiszkb03kf3n9o88sdfifk&amp;amp;st=do7a8866&amp;amp;raw=1" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/c20b8f24-2486-4074-bd9a-5bc88f0d1d6b.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364042894"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3312896">UsLaynes</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found today by a Utahn while on vacation. I will add more later. Did a mass change of TB's

SL TFTlletterboxC

Turning Green Boxes (and blue envelopes) Into Smileys One Find At A Time And Enjoying The Adventure Along The Way!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363290617"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T12:23:29</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="9366409">rickdorsey8080</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Made the odyssey to find my 41st Odyssey in Oregon on Sunday morning. The journey went from Rhode Island to Boston to Portland to Corvallis to the Oregon Coast . Finally made it to the lighthouse area, signed the log,  stamped my passport and basked in the sunshine.This is my 3rd Odyssey in the Northwest Region. Dropped off a coin and grabbed a TB. Celebrated with a chocolate chunk cookie. FP added, Tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363257782"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T10:50:22</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="629831">RMx2</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nice, big cache!  Left lots of swag 😊</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362907746"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T09:38:35</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="53101776">ratsx06</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Super fun cache with lots of swag! TFTH!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364231349"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-14T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5892168">TTO2</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This was our first West Coast cache. We were sad the entire area shops and buildings were shut down to replace a water main, but you as a CO CO were smart to have a 24/7 cache container. You don't know how many geocachers are going after this series tell me that places are closed even though the posted hours indicate that they're open. We now have four locations we were victims to this situation. One of them, the last one, we even called ahead, and they told us "maybe" they would be open. They were not, and we drove 200 miles out of the way to get it. 

Oregon facts we learned while geocaching:

* Oregon’s state flag pictures a beaver on its reverse side. It is the only state flag to carry two separate designs.
* Oregon has historically been famous for having more ghost towns than any other state, with over 60 deserted mining communities.
* Crater Lake is the deepest lake in the United States and is formed in the remains of an ancient volcano.
* Oregon and New Jersey were long famous as the only states without self-serve gas stations, preserving a unique heritage of full-service pump attendants.
* At 8,000 feet deep Hells Canyon is the deepest river gorge in North America.
* The hazelnut is Oregon’s official state nut. Oregon is the only state that has an official state nut. The hazelnut is also known as the filbert.
* Navy blue and gold are Oregon’s official state colors.
* The Chinook salmon is Oregon’s official state fish.
* In 1880 a sea cave was discovered near what is now known as Florence. Sea Lion Caves is known to be the largest sea cave in the world.
* The nation’s most photographed lighthouse is the Heceta Head Lighthouse located in Lane County.
* Darlingtonia Wayside is Oregon’s only rare plant sanctuary.
* Oregon’s second-highest waterfall is Salt Creek Falls in the Cascade Mountain range. It drops 286 feet.
* The H.J. Andrews Experimental Forest is one of the largest long-term ecological research sites in the United States.
* Eugene is rated by “Bicycling Magazine” as one of the top ten cycling communities in the United States.
* There are nine lighthouses standing along the coastline. Five are still being used; the others are designated historic monuments.
* Portland is an example of outstanding urban planning. The city is known as The City of Roses.
* High above the city of Portland the International Rose Test Garden features more than 500 varieties of roses cultivated continuously since 1917.
* At 11,239 feet Mount Hood stands as the tallest peak in Oregon. Mount Hood is a dormant volcano.
* Silver Falls State Park is the Oregon’s largest state park. It features 10 waterfalls and contains a wide variety of forested hiking trails.
* Crater Lake is the deepest lake in the United States. It was formed more than 6,500 years ago. Its crystal-blue waters are world renowned.
* Discovered in 1874 the caves located in Oregon Caves National Monument are carved within solid marble.
* The world’s largest rosary collection is exhibited at The Columbia Gorge Interpretive Center. A local resident collected the exhibit.
* The Carousel Museum contains the world’s largest and most comprehensive collection of carousel horses.
* Fort Clatsop National Memorial contains a replica of Lewis and Clark’s 1805-1806 winter outpost.
* The small village of Bickelton is filled with bluebird houses seen on the posts of every house.
* The Columbia Gorge National Scenic Area is a spectacular river canyon cutting the only sea-level route through the Cascade Mountain Range.
* The Ries-Thompson House is the oldest remaining residence in Parkdale. Built circa 1900 the home and area offer a commanding view of Mount Hood.
* Tillamook is home to Oregon’s largest cheese factory.
* Florence is known as Oregon’s rhododendron capital.
* The Oregon Legislature designated the Oregon Grape (Mahonia aquifolium) as the Oregon state flower by resolution in 1899.
* Oregon’s capitol building is located in Salem. Earlier capitals include the cities of Oregon City and Corvallis.
* The Columbia River forms most of the northern border between Oregon and Washington.
* The Snake River forms over half of the eastern boundary with Idaho.
* In 1905 the largest log cabin in the world was built in Portland to honor the Lewis and Clark expedition.
* A treaty between the United States and Spain established the current southern border between Oregon and California. The treaty was signed in 1819.
* The Tillamook Naval Air Museum is housed in the world’s largest wooden clear-span building.
* Oregon is home to the single largest living organism on Earth, a massive honey fungus (Armillaria ostoyae) spanning over 2,385 acres in the Malheur National Forest.
* Mill Ends Park in Portland is recognized by the Guinness Book of World Records as the smallest park in the world, measuring a tiny two feet across.
* The city of Portland was named by a coin toss in 1845 between Francis Pettygrove and Asa Lovejoy; if the coin had landed differently, it would be named Boston</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="44.003867" lon="-70.99285"><time>2024-12-27T00:00:00</time><name>GCAZTTG</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Maine by yukionna</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCAZTTG</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Maine</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9742636" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Maine</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>yukionna</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1598716">yukionna</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="0">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="55" inc="1">Short hike (&lt;1 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="47" inc="1">Field puzzle</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="33" inc="1">Motorcycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="31" inc="0">Camping nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="17" inc="0">Poisonous plants</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Maine</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/085ef39f-7673-44fc-945f-3579422587dc.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/5aaad139-9287-4001-be98-a713444033a5.jpg" style="height:463px;width:750px;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How to find the geocache&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The cache is not located at the posted coordinates but it is a good place to park. From the posted coordinates, walk about 100&amp;#39; northeast which will bring you to an information sign. Look at the top of the sign for the name of the trail system.  Enter all the words into the certitude checker below to obtain information about finding the cache.  The words can be entered in any case and with or without blank spaces.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div style="text-align:center;"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.certitudes.org/certitude?wp=GCAZTTG"&gt;&lt;img src="https://www.certitudes.org/logo?wp=GCAZTTG" title="Click to access the certitude checker" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please note that the cache is only available when the visitor center is open so plan your visit accordingly.  You must sign the log in order to log this cache as found.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Visitor center summer hours (Memorial Day - Columbus Day): 8:00 AM - 6:00 PM, 7 days a week&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Visitor center off season hours: 9:00 AM - 5:30 PM, 7 days a week&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The visitor center is closed on Thanksgiving and Christmas Day. &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What to do when you find the geocache&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The cache is a letterbox hybrid which means it is a letterbox and a geocache.  It  contains two different stamps: the Cache Odyssey Maine self-inking stamp and a second Maine-themed stamp with a stamp pad.  If you would like to keep track of the Northeast states you visit in the geotour, download a copy of the &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.geocaching.com/play/geotours/cacheodyssey-northeast"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#2980b9;"&gt;Northeast Region Passbook&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; or scan the QR code below. Use the Cache Odyssey Maine stamp, to stamp the &amp;quot;Maine&amp;quot; box in the passport.  If you have a personal stamp, you are welcome to stamp the cache logbook with your stamp.  Don&amp;#39;t forget to sign the cache logbook too!  If you don&amp;#39;t have a personal stamp, you can just sign the cache logbook.  Please leave both stamps in the cache container for the next visitor to use.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div style="text-align:center;"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NORTHEAST REGION&lt;br /&gt;
GEOTOUR PASSPORT&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/a6d9ae76-3867-42f1-98c5-4484c7ffa5f6.jpg" style="height:150px;width:150px;" /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="font-size:10px;"&gt;Scan to download&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Once you visit all eleven caches in the Northeast geotour, you will earn a digital souvenir from Groundspeak.  You can learn more about all the geotours below.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fryeburg Visitor Center&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Maine State Visitor Information Center is located on Maine&amp;#39;s western border on route 302 east in Fryeburg. The information center is professionally staffed with Travel Counselors offering information about destinations, accommodations, services, and travel conditions statewide. Maine maps, guides, and other publications are offered free of charge. Visitors can relax at the picnic tables or take a walk on the 4 mile Mountain Division Trail which begins right at the parking lot. There is free WIFI available for all to use, water fountains, and bathrooms. Photo opportunities are available inside in the rocking chairs with the Moose or at the kids picnic table!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" style="width:80%;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Northeast Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/76de9cdc-8b3c-4816-8280-2fbc61852b60.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/18d9b309-a90c-4900-a735-2eedd7912009.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/0f404634-c476-4cd5-b8df-f85d6aa8069e.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/dc93f2f7-97ae-4cb4-a9e1-8986f081414f.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/179e8963-86e3-49a1-bc17-fd28c53b735a.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/f6ab1d02-9794-4521-955f-0bcf19e3c566.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/ba935c3f-3961-459a-a950-8b1462cbe818.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:24px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Leaderboard&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Cell coverage can be spotty here.  If you can’t connect online to the Certitude checker, you can find the cache inside the visitor center on the counter.  Look for the large lobster trap letterbox.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364252927"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:34:05</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18887023">SweetSuzie558</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thank you for the Cache Odyssey cache. Now that is a cache container!  </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364196151"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="9840965">The Lowry 6</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found It! We came up to join the White Mountain Breakfast Club and grabbed a few smileys while we were here. Since we were so close we crossed the border for this one. Traded trackables while we were here. TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363744136"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T12:57:01</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8724011">Candy Apple 68</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Clever container!!  Greetings from Letchworth State Park in Mount Morris, NY! :)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363959976"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5445477">Albus_Birch</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Made short work of the checker, and then headed after the cache.  WOW!  Cool setup with an extra stamp!

Favorite point!

8058</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362684942"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-22T14:12:21</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="680794">Salmonelas</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC! Found together with Arodama.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="36.806317" lon="-114.07"><time>2024-11-01T00:00:00</time><name>GCB00W8</name><desc>CACHE ODYSSEY - NEVADA by Pathfinder33</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB00W8</url><urlname>CACHE ODYSSEY - NEVADA</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9748456" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>CACHE ODYSSEY - NEVADA</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Pathfinder33</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="3130126">Pathfinder33</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="47" inc="1">Field puzzle</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="1">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="33" inc="1">Motorcycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="34" inc="1">Quads</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="35" inc="1">Off-road vehicles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="46" inc="1">Trucks/RVs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Nevada</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b7be9a3d-4cd6-45a8-a96e-a3a45b233f37.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At the posted coordinates you will find yourself at an intersection of a sidewalk and a walking path next to a picnic table. You must follow the directions given to find the Letterbox Hybrid Geocache. You will need to count paces to get to the final container. A pace is, when standing with your feet together, you take a step with your right foot, and then with your left. When your left foot hits the ground that is one pace (two steps). The average step is roughly 15&amp;quot;, so the average pace is 30&amp;quot; give or take. Someone with longer then average legs will have a longer pace, and someone with shorter than average legs will have a shorter pace. We will be using the &amp;quot;average&amp;quot; pace for this, and don&amp;#39;t worry I will give you helpers along the way to keep you on track.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Start by walking slightly downhill at 51° for 7 paces. You should now be in the middle of the walking path.&lt;br /&gt;
You now need to turn to 171° and walk for 88 paces. Along the way at roughly pace 58 you should have a burned tree stump directly to your left. And at roughly pace 72 you will encounter the first of 3 sets of Zebra Stripes. The Zebra Stripes should protect you from any fast moving dangers that may run into you in this area.&lt;br /&gt;
Once you have completed all 88 paces, you will need to turn to face 261° and walk for 14 paces. You will cross the second set of Zebra Stripes here.&lt;br /&gt;
You will need to now turn to 261° and walk for 22 paces. You will cross the third set of Zebra Stripes during this leg of the quest.&lt;br /&gt;
You now need to turn to face 163° and walk for 6 paces. You will go through 2 sets of magic doors that work on their own, and pass between 3 clear plastic towers. Once you make it through the three clear plastic towers, the geocache will be directly on your right 2 paces.  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As this is a Letterbox Hybrid Geocache, the stamp inside the container must remain in the cache, it is not SWAG for trading. If you have a personal stamp feel free to stamp the logbook.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is no need to interact with the staff at the final location. They are aware of the container and will leave you be as you interact with it. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Letterbox Hybrid Geocache is available:&lt;br /&gt;
Monday - Thursday: 10:00AM to 7:00PM &lt;br /&gt;
Friday - Saturday 10:00AM to 6:00PM&lt;br /&gt;
Sunday: 1:00PM to 5:00PM&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Southwest Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b19ba586-1a55-44b3-8eb2-0781c0a8e99a.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;RetiredGuy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>It's the "Big Box of Books"</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364253817"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="26101408">Tw33k27</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Cache found, log signed, and cache replaced in good condition. 

Grabbed this one on my way to Vegas for my daughter's softball tournament. 

It's not the destination that keeps me going. It's the journey and memories of all the fun caches I find along the way.  TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361025528"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-14T21:36:37</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="765427">razorbackgirl</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">What an incredibly well made cache! We were on our way from Vegas to Zion and couldn't pass up this excellent cache. Thanks for putting so much thought and working into making it! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360480699"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-11T12:18:04</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="609455">Data Wrangler</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Fun cache. Took a minute to solve the puzzle, then put ink on the log! I should finish the Southwest Region GeoTour on this pre-GWXXII trip. Favorite. SL, TFTC.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359827227"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-08T14:36:39</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3001434">Tag-along2</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Out with third wheel grabbing some Mysteries and caches and working on my suntan interesting box thanks for the cache. signed log</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360369414"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-08T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2363744">daphm</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">It took a few tries to get the right order, but after that everything went smoothly. Loved the paint job on the outside! TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="39.996" lon="-82.675033"><time>2025-01-08T00:00:00</time><name>GCB0MWZ</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Ohio by KBLAST</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB0MWZ</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Ohio</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9767698" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Ohio</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>KBLAST</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1691008">KBLAST</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="55" inc="1">Short hike (&lt;1 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="47" inc="1">Field puzzle</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="62" inc="1">Seasonal access</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Ohio</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/ca87c6ff-e691-4737-b5ca-aaae1d57933b.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This Ohio Letterbox Information!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is a letterbox hybrid geocache. Inside it you will find a red ammo box containing the Cache Odyssey Ohio self-inking stamp and a logbook. If you have a personal stamp, please stamp the logbook with your stamp. You can just sign the logbook if you don&amp;#39;t have a personal stamp. The stamp and logbook are to remain in the letterbox hybrid for the next visitor to use. You will also find an orange ammo can that will be the home for trackables, so this is also essentially a Travel Bug Hotel!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;FTF Honors go to GeoHAMgamer! Congratulations!!!&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To find this Cache:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step 1: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Go to the posted coordinates.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step 2: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Upon arrival, if you do NOT see Spiderman at or near the posted coordinates, the nearby location is closed. Hours are listed below if you are interested. &lt;strong&gt;Whether it is open or closed&lt;/strong&gt;, head southeast to the bright green door. Take note of the first digit of the number in front of S. Main (on the same line). &lt;strong&gt;This is the first digit of the lock on the geocache.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step 3: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To the right of the large window of the main shop, there is a thermometer. How much is a shave and a haircut? Subtract 20. &lt;strong&gt;This is the second digit of the lock on the geocache.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the bottom left corner of the large window is a brand name that starts with the letter &amp;#39;K&amp;#39;. How many letters are in that brand name? &lt;strong&gt;This number is the third digit of the lock on the geocache.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step 5: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Back at the green door, there is a lower window pane. Below the Pac-man, ghosts, and Jurassic Park symbol, there is a white number in a white circle. Remove the fraction portion of the mixed number. What is the remaining whole number? &lt;strong&gt;This is the fourth and final digit of the lock on the geocache.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step 6: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Look down in front of the main window to find the geocache! Turn the numbers so that the 4 digits are in order between the words Master and Lock on the lock. &lt;strong&gt;When finished, please replace the lock so that the Master and Lock are facing forward for the next finder. Make sure the numbers are showing and that the shackle closes all the way, then spin the numbers to lock it again.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Optional Fun!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS IS NOT REQUIRED!!!!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You will see the Cache Odyssey stickers on the outside of this chest. You will also see other stickers! Please feel free to bring or purchase your own stickers and add them to the container, then take a picture of the cache showing off your contribution and post it in your log!!! My hope is that some day this cache will look completely different than it started!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The location hours are:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Monday, Wednesday - Saturday 11am - 7pm and Sunday 12pm - 5pm. Closed Tuesday. Feel free to call 740-951-0099 if you want to verify hours before arriving.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is the before picture:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/0f40196a-3255-461c-9394-a6bf4e5c0d82.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the East Central Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b19ba586-1a55-44b3-8eb2-0781c0a8e99a.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;RetiredGuy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>If you are having any troubles during business hours, the people working at this location will be happy to help you out! If you don't see the chest out front under the window, something is horribly wrong. Please post a Needs Maintenance.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364901742"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1223249">sciwiz1</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">The whole team is out today to get to milestone 13000 and this one was IT!  Spotted the cache as we parked and after exiting our car we quickly went to work looking for the clues to the combo.  Got our numbers and spun the lock ... but nope. Tried a few more things, but still couldn't unlock.  Finally, started over with figuring the numbers and quickly found an error on our part. Tried with the correct combo and everything work perfectly. Signed the log and put a sticker on the chest.  As we were just finishing up the shop owner popped out to check on us and say hello. Thank you to the owner for hosting this unique cache and this one gets a fav point! TNLNSL TFTC (#13000).</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364439411"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T15:18:37</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="55516414">astermer1</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">So cool</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364493347"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3797805">mrahudson</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Dipping 2 trackables I picked up here that were not in the inventory.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364399907"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3797805">mrahudson</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">7th Cache Odyssey find!  Did a 4 for 4 trackable swap, grabbed a Pathtag and left a few and dropped a couple trackable event cards.  The store owner came out to make sure we got in fine, which we did.  Great stop along this road trip.  Favorite point!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364399011"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3791981">mrsahudson</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Great find and great place. This is our seventh Cache Odyssey thanks, favorite!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="60.554967" lon="-151.2612"><time>2024-12-29T00:00:00</time><name>GCB09MA</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Alaska by GeocacheAlaska! Inc. &amp; SSO JOAT</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB09MA</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Alaska</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9756890" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Alaska</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>GeocacheAlaska! Inc. &amp; SSO JOAT</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="850185">GeocacheAlaska!</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="47" inc="1">Field puzzle</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Alaska</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/81da709c-264b-4f44-9ec4-01116521d8bb.png" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Welcome to the &lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey - Alaska&lt;/strong&gt; cache, which is part of the official Northwest Cache Odyssey GeoTour series. You will need to find the Cache Odyssey cache in each of Six (6) of the Northwest United States to complete this GeoTour. The Alaska cache is located inside of the Kenai Chamber of Commerce Visitor Center, which is only accessible during business hours. The Visitor Center is open year round with different summer and winter hours. The Visitor Center is also closed from Christmas through New Years. Check the Visitor Center website event calendar for more information on operating times and closures.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;Summer hours (Memorial Day to Labor Day)&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Monday - Friday 9AM - 6PM&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Saturday 10AM - 5PM&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sunday 12PM - 5PM&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;Winter hours (Labor Day to Memorial Day)&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Monday - Friday 9AM - 5PM&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Saturday - Closed&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sunday - Closed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.kenaichamber.org/about-us.html" target="_blank"&gt;Kenai Chamber of Commerce Visitor Center&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; 

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://gcak.org" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/5b8985f3-e6a3-4ea4-938b-a0ec94f44635_l.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;How to Find the Cache&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;Start at the Published Coordinates out in the parking lot!&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;This is a Gadget Cache that requires you to manipulate some pieces on the container to unlock it for access to the inside. You&amp;#39;ll need a number code. You&amp;#39;ll find this code by carefully reading about a guy named Petr at the published coordinates for this cache. The code question is, in what year did Petr visit a nearby Trading Post while exploring the Kenai Peninsula?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After finding the answer to the question above, navigate to the Cache Access Point coordinates in the Waypoint list for this cache. After passing through this double portal into the lobby, your GPS will become ineffective. As you look around, there are four (4) corridors or doorways leaving the lobby to the interior of the building. Look for the one just to the right of a pair of white Oldsquaw ducks resting on a wall platform. There is also a pair of Magpies resting on a stump above the corridor. When you enter this corridor, you&amp;#39;ll want to search the first alcove to your left.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To get detailed directions to the cache with a spoiler hint on how to open the container, go to the following Certitude link and enter Petr&amp;#39;s last name.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.certitudes.org/certitude?wp=GCB09MA" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;img src="https://www.certitudes.org/logo?wp=GCB09MA" title="Click to see the list of solvers" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;div style="font-family:Comic Sans MS;"&gt;You can validate your solution with &lt;a href="https://www.certitudes.org/certitude?wp=GCB09MA"&gt;certitude&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This cache contains a self-inking Letterbox Stamp. The Stamp is NOT a trade item and must remain inside the cache. If you carry a personal logbook for Letterboxing, use this custom stamp to mark your log and use your personal stamp to mark the logbook in this cache. You may also use it to stamp your Northwest GeoTour passport, though this is not required to get credit for finding this cache.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This cache is placed with full permission from the Executive Director and the Staff is aware of its presence. You do not need to use stealth to find it. If you have difficulty solving the code to access the cache, you may ask Staff or send a message to the Cache Owner. We want you to find it and solve the easy puzzle to access it. If there are any problems with the cache, you may send a direct message to the Cache Owner or to local cacher &lt;a href="https://www.geocaching.com/p/?guid=d8cbf6b1-c723-4519-ac1c-2de2fc93df2c"&gt;SSO JOAT&lt;/a&gt; so we can get things back in order right away.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After opening the cache and signing the logbook, please replace the contents exactly as found. You must leave the code entered into the mechanism until you have closed the door. Once the door is shut, please return all parts of the mechanism back to their closed position.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please trade fair. However, you should see a number of small gold coins in the trade bin. Every finder may take ONE coin as a souvenir of finding this cache.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Are you traveling from out of state for this cache? If you are arriving in Anchorage, you can get here by air or highway. The highway is a roughly 150-mile drive from Anchorage that will take about 3 hours, each way. To fly in, look for commuter flights to the Kenai airport. Flights between Anchorage and Kenai are frequent throughout the day. Once at the Kenai airport, you could take a taxi cab or even walk to the cache. It&amp;#39;s only one mile with a nice sidewalk the whole way.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you're driving to the Kenai from Anchorage, have a look at the official KMTA GeoTrail series that runs from Girdwood to Hope to Cooper Landing to Seward along the Seward and Sterling Highways. &lt;a href="https://www.geocaching.com/plan/lists/BMCC06Z"&gt;KMTA GeoTrail Bookmark List&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt; 

&lt;p&gt;We hope that you enjoy your experience enough to write a fun log of your adventures, however we respectfully ask that you do NOT post any hints or spoilers in your online log or post any photos of the cache or the objects located at the published coordinates that you used to solve the access code. Logs with spoilers or spoiler images will be immediately removed without warning and we&amp;#39;ll ask you to write a new log without spoilers. Thank you for keeping the game fun for everyone!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To get credit for finding a GeoTour cache, you must legibly enter your geocaching handle into the logbook inside the cache. Finds claimed without a physical logbook entry will be removed, per GCHQ guidelines.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;!--start of handicaching link--&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;a href="http://www.handicaching.com/show.php?waypoint=GCB09MA" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.handicaching.com/images/seal_rater2.gif" border="0" alt="View the ratings for GCB09MA" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;!--end of handicaching link--&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Northwest Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b19ba586-1a55-44b3-8eb2-0781c0a8e99a.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;RetiredGuy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>[Puzzle Lock:] Enter from the front after sliding in the code - No need for any keys</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364258100"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T14:51:37</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8814283">TheLF</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Continuing my Odyssey quest after GeoWoodstock in Hutchinson, KS. I may get home in 3 weeks, and then again, I may not. I’m a geocacher and retired.😎.          My Odyssey #43
**********

2 WOWs on this one.  Favorite point for sure.
1.  I’m the first finder in 2026
2.  What a great job on constructing this host.  Very clever locking system.
Landed at 9:41am and headed toward Kenai right from the car rental booth. With no sleep last night, I was tired and hungry when I arrived at GZ, but first things first.,😂.  After finding this great cache, I’m not hungry or tired… just excited to be one more find closer to my goal of completing this series on this trip.
The cache page shows 7 TBs in residence, but I’m discovering 14. I guess a few were dropped last year and not logged. Hopefully this will get some of them in right standing with the owners. 
Thanks so much for making my trip to Alaska a memorable one, with this fun and clever hide.
I have so many friends that I wish were on this trip with me…. Mainly because I’ll have to repeat these caching stories over and over 😂🤣😎.
Thanks again for a fun adventure.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1341861351"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-14T20:44:38</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="52914625">BirkenstockReport</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hey y’all! If you’re looking at this cache because you’re planning your summer Alaskan adventures and aren’t sure where to start, message me! I’m happy to help with advice on how to get to Kenai, logistics, other caches to check out, general tourist info, and overall geocaching fun in the last frontier!! Cache on! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1337051112"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-06T12:59:34</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="29796244">DarlingKitsune</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thank you! Awesome cashe.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1335462475"><groundspeak:date>2025-11-21T14:46:07</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="45698589">Gonewiththewin</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Up from the Tampa Bay Florida with Team_Conway with our Alaska geo-friends Rspace and LBK 
Love the container 
Favorite point 
TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1335768306"><groundspeak:date>2025-11-21T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="272513">Ladybug Kids</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I teamed up with RSPace and Floridian cachers Gonewiththewin and Team_Conway, for a run to Kenai for Alaska's Cache Odyssey cache.  We made a day of the effort, starting with Sno-Blow, caching to Kenai, logging the Odyssey, and wrapping up with [Team_Conway's 50th State Event](https://coord.info/GCBB6CX).  It was around 1445 when we arrived after spending about seven hours to complete the pilgrimage for Team_Conway's 36th logged Cache Odyssey, which places him eighth on the leaderboard.  Team_Conway dove straight into cracking the safe while the rest of us watched him perform the necessary manipulations to access the all important logbook.  Soon we were signing and stamping the large ledger, checking on the resident trackables, and admiring the container's craftsmanship.  I highly recommend that visitors step into the "museum" part of the visitor center because it provides a short, but nice overview of the local history including the monster snag extracted from the Kenai River that captured thousands of lures prior to its removal.  The animal mounts in the entryway are also interesting, especially the raptors that are mounted with spread wings which provide a sense of how majestic and powerful those birds are.   We also chatted up the young man at the desk about caribou and moose hunting and salmon fishing before hitting the road home.  I detoured back to Soldotna via Bridge Access Road and Kalifornsky Beach Road in the hopes of spotting caribou on the flats, but they played hard to get today.  We had an uneventful drive back to Anchorage despite the weather throwing rain, sleet, snow, and wind at us between Cooper Landing and the big city, arriving back in time for burgers at Arctic Roadrunner before the event.  Favorite point awarded.  Thank you for the cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="20.230167" lon="-155.797917"><time>2024-11-18T00:00:00</time><name>GCB0GVP</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - HAWAII by DTXHEGARTY</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB0GVP</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - HAWAII</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9763815" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - HAWAII</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>DTXHEGARTY</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="11678325">DTXPHEGARTY</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="59" inc="1">Food nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="1">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Hawaii</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Welcome To North Kohala And &amp;quot;Cache Odyssey&amp;quot;!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;What is &amp;quot;Cache Odyssey&amp;quot;?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&amp;quot;Cache Odyssey&amp;quot; is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a unique, highly creative letterbox geocache to every state.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;What&amp;#39;s the Mission Behind &amp;quot;Cache Odyssey&amp;quot;?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This isn&amp;#39;t your average cache series! We&amp;#39;re here to prove that Geocaching is a game/hobby for everyone; no matter your physical abilities or location. Cache Odyssey aims to show that Terrain 1 caches can be just as daring and innovative as the most challenging hides. Because after all, not every adventure needs to be a D5T5!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;What makes &amp;quot;Cache Odyssey special?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;When you embark on a &amp;quot;Cache Odyssey&amp;quot; adventure, you can expect:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;The &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kamehameha I&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; statue (original cast) is an &lt;a href="https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Outdoor_sculpture" title="Outdoor sculpture"&gt;outdoor sculpture&lt;/a&gt; by American artist &lt;a href="https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thomas_Ridgeway_Gould" title="Thomas Ridgeway Gould"&gt;Thomas Ridgeway Gould&lt;/a&gt;, cast in 1880 and installed in 1883. It stands in front of the old country courthouse in the town of &lt;a href="https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kapaau,_Hawaii" title="Kapaau, Hawaii"&gt;Kapaʻau&lt;/a&gt;, located in &lt;a href="https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Kohala" title="North Kohala"&gt;North Kohala&lt;/a&gt; on the &lt;a href="https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Island_of_Hawai%CA%BBi" title="Island of Hawaiʻi"&gt;Island of Hawaiʻi&lt;/a&gt;. Made of cast &lt;a href="https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brass" title="Brass"&gt;brass&lt;/a&gt; and painted with lifelike colors, it depicts &lt;a href="https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kamehameha_I" title="Kamehameha I"&gt;Kamehameha I&lt;/a&gt;, and represents an important cultural and spiritual object for the local community&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part; there&amp;#39;s a &amp;quot;Cache Odyssey&amp;quot; hide in Every State! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; That&amp;#39;s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;*Challenge yourself to find more &amp;quot;Cache Odyssey&amp;quot; caches across the country, or maybe even plan to collect them all! Feeling adventurous? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Check out the &amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.geocachetalk.com/oddessy" style="text-decoration:none;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#1155cc;"&gt;&lt;u&gt;www.geocachetalk.com/odyssey&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;full list of locations&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt; and start planning your geocaching quest today.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Start Your Cache Odyssey Adventure!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Ready to hit the road? Whether you&amp;#39;re a seasoned geocacher or a curious newcomer, there&amp;#39;s an adventure waiting for you in every state. Begin your journey today and see just how fun, accessible, and creative geocaching can be.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Happy Caching, and remember: &amp;quot;The Journey Is The Destination!&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Tethered To A Tree, Hidden Away From MUGGLES.
Lock Code: (Hawaii’s 3 Digit AREA CODE)</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1307148852"><groundspeak:date>2025-06-26T07:04:32</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3726515">TeamPumpJack</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Check out the replacement 

GCB8YFB</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1307055574"><groundspeak:date>2025-06-25T14:46:40</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11678325">DTXPHEGARTY</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">So Sorry Geocaching Friends &amp; Family.
Due To A Work Injury &amp; Cache Being Muggled…
I Will Be Archiving This Cache Odyssey - Hawaii Cache.
With My Sincerest Apologies…
DTXHEGARTY </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1305622428"><groundspeak:date>2025-06-18T08:47:05</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="39714428">baszabo</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Came to find this and still not available! Darn muggles!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1302762512"><groundspeak:date>2025-06-03T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3265080">cbagaason</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I really hope this one is up and running soon while I am in the islands for two weeks. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1299215420"><groundspeak:date>2025-05-18T03:19:52</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8032860">TruStar</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I HOPE THIS IS FIXED IN THE NEXT 24 HOURS!!! I have a flight booked for tomorrow. And as Eminem said, "I only get one shot! ONE CHANCE!!!"</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="39.06625" lon="-94.5915"><time>2025-01-20T00:00:00</time><name>GC859C7</name><desc>CACHE ODYSSEY - MISSOURI by OwenfromKC</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC859C7</url><urlname>CACHE ODYSSEY - MISSOURI</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="7135031" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>CACHE ODYSSEY - MISSOURI</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>OwenfromKC</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="605980">OwenfromKC</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="53" inc="0">Park and grab</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="55" inc="1">Short hike (&lt;1 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="47" inc="1">Field puzzle</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="14" inc="0">Recommended at night</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="26" inc="1">Public transportation nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="33" inc="1">Motorcycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Missouri</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/658927b0-9a5b-4e7d-866f-3f28bcfc6995.png" width="100%" /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;center&gt;
&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;font color="#991A1E"&gt;Much THANKS to the&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Veterans Of Foreign Wars&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
for their assistance in hosting this Cache Odyssey Geocache.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;


&lt;font size="9"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffd700"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;

&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="#991a1e"&gt;PERMISSION HAS BEEN GRANTED FOR THIS LOCATION BY BOTH&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="#00000"&gt;Quartermaster General of VFW National Headquarters&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="#00000"&gt;&amp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="#00000"&gt;Director of VFW Properties&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;font size="9"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="#ffd700"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;

&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;font color="red"&gt;This ODYSSEY is a&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;marquee behavior="alternate" loop="0" width="70%"&gt;&lt;font size="7"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="red"&gt;S&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;font color="red"&gt;&lt;font size="5"&gt;EARCH &lt;/font&gt;&lt;b&gt;. A&lt;/b&gt;&lt;font size="5"&gt;ND&lt;/font&gt;&lt;b&gt; . R&lt;/b&gt;&lt;font size="5"&gt;ESCUE&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/marquee&gt; 
&lt;br /&gt;

&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;font color="red"&gt;Mission&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
We may have a fallen comrade!&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Luckily, our friend left detailed notes of the planned patrol route.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Your elite expertise is needed to locate one of our nation's greatest treasures.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
This mission will require you to negotiate an urban environment, interpret hidden meanings, and utilize the unique communication abilities that you have developed as an elite operator of the geocache community.
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Only your highly-honed skills and rare determination will result in a successful mission. I trust you will display the intestinal fortitude required to fight on to the objective and complete the mission
&lt;br /&gt;though you be the lone survivor.
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;div style="border-radius:20px;border:20px solid #991a1e;margin-bottom:5px;padding:5px;"&gt;
&lt;div style="border-radius:15px;border:10px solid #ffd700;margin-bottom:0px;padding:5px;"&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;font color="#00000"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;
1. First, secure your transportation in the motor pool. Prepare to exit the ACP but you got to ruck up. The signs say no CMV, EFV, FAV, LTVR or ball playing.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
2. Grab your gear. Proceed to the Rally Point located by the natural wooden structure (it's a tree) marked on your map.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
3. From the RP face due east. You will IMMEDIATELY see a dangerous crossing. Make sure OpFor doesn&amp;#39;t spot you and you can cross safely. (Parking entrance. Do Not cross Broadway. Think small scale.)&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
4. Pass an open field and next you will encounter rough terrain riddled with boulders. A stone wall is also at your 3 o'clock. It's a choke point. There is only way through here.
&lt;br /&gt;
Stay alert. Stay alive.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
5. Soon the wall will turn south near another long field. This may be the most dangerous area you encounter. It has been known to be full of land mines. The locals even erected a green &amp; white sign warning everyone who passes of the high price these landmines can cost.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
6. Once you see the green &amp; white sign on the field, a half-moon shaped grove of bushes nearby can provide a safe haven from those dirty dogs laying the mines. Better to go there now and not be here when they return.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
We believe our friend is somewhere beyond the forest to the North.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
7. From the half-moon grove our comrade took a bearing of 356 degrees traversing another danger zone! An LDA, a Linear Danger Area. Scroll The Road!  (Check your bearing. Do Not cross Broadway.)&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
8. You should pass another strange half-moon shaped grove on your right and several other odd-shaped fields and groves to your left. Be sure to utilize the tree cover as you negotiate the terrain through here.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
9. Ahead you see dark figures. Two stoic gentlemen appear to be moving towards you. Why are they here? If you take the time, they will communicate their mission to you. It reflects our mission here; how to help another individual.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
10. Study your surroundings. Other figures will come into view. When two families are in your vision, you are on the correct path.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
11. The torch of liberty continues to provide a guiding light on this mission.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
12. When you have sacred ground on both sides of you, you&amp;#39;ll know you are on the correct heading.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
13. Next, you will discover a different kind of field up on a geometric plane where poppies blow in the wind.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
14. You are almost at the end of the patrol route so our comrade must be in the area. Soon you notice 4 gentlemen nearby. Perhaps one of them knows the whereabouts of our missing patriot.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Are any of them are locals? Maybe one of them is familiar with this area.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
15. Wait. There is someone else at this place. A fifth person, here, with them. His face is not visible like the others but he is here. You can sense him in the dark grey fog; being stealthy and blending into the background. Somewhere... hiding in plane sight.
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
 
&lt;center&gt;&lt;font color="red"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS IS VITAL TO THE SUCCESS OF THE MISSION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
16. When you locate this shadowy individual, you &lt;font color="red"&gt;NEED&lt;/font&gt; to check his code name&lt;br /&gt;
against our &lt;font color="red"&gt;A.L.I.A.S. &lt;/font&gt;list.&lt;br /&gt;
(&lt;font color="red"&gt;A&lt;/font&gt;rea &lt;font color="red"&gt;L&lt;/font&gt;ocal &lt;font color="red"&gt;I&lt;/font&gt;nformant &lt;font color="red"&gt;A&lt;/font&gt;nd &lt;font color="red"&gt;S&lt;/font&gt;ources list).&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
17. The secret file folder below links to our cleverly disguised online database of secret agent identities.
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
If his name is in our database, you will receive actionable intel from him necessary to rescue one of our nation's greatest treasures.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Hopefully you will discover our comrade still standing proud, on guard, and ever vigilant! 
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;center&gt;
&lt;font color="red"&gt;YOU DO NOT NEED TO TOUCH OR&lt;br /&gt;
USE ANY FORCE WHEN YOU FIND OUR COMRADE&lt;br /&gt;
RESPECT THE PERSONAL SPACE OF OUR FRIEND IN UNIFORM&lt;br /&gt;
WE DON'T WANT TO LOSE ANYONE TO FRIENDLY FIRE!&lt;/font&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
You must utilize the intel gained from the database file folder.&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
 
&lt;div style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.certitudes.org/certitude?wp=GC859C7"&gt;&lt;img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/44b709c5-8d2d-4df8-8307-937db1413b43_l.jpg" title="Click to see the list of your fellow volunteers" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;div style="font-family:Comic Sans MS;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:medium;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:black;"&gt;To find our comrade, enter the agent's code name into the database &lt;a href="https://www.certitudes.org/certitude?wp=GC859C7"&gt;A.L.I.A.S.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;span style="font-size:medium;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:black;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;

&lt;center&gt;Thank you for volunteering on this epic S.A.R. mission.&lt;br /&gt;
Your participation has been noted and will not be forgotten.&lt;/center&gt;

&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;center&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey!&lt;/center&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;


&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; geocache to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt; to all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Midwest Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:11pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b19ba586-1a55-44b3-8eb2-0781c0a8e99a.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;RetiredGuy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="list-style-type:disc;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;!-- MIDWEST GEOTOUR --&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://cacheodyssey.com/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/aab13929-d1bd-4644-a7d2-a31db45d2706_l.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;a href="https://info.flagcounter.com/0ir0"&gt;&lt;img alt="Flag Counter" src="https://s05.flagcounter.com/countxl_US/0ir0/bg_FFFFFF/txt_000000/border_991A1E/columns_8/maxflags_55/viewers_Patriots/labels_1/pageviews_1/flags_0/percent_0/" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;a href="https://info.flagcounter.com/dd1G"&gt;&lt;img alt="Flag Counter" src="https://s01.flagcounter.com/countxl/dd1G/bg_FFFFFF/txt_000000/border_FFD700/columns_8/maxflags_250/viewers_Allies/labels_1/pageviews_1/flags_0/percent_0/" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>[DO NOT TOUCH OUR COMRADE! DO NOT FORCE ANYTHING!  You must follow the directions to the end and use the information from the checker to gain access.]</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364911652"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1639892">Uncle Fuzzy</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Gal &amp; I just found out about the Odyssey Caches last year. Just making our rounds we’ve been to over a dozen of them now. We have seen some nice, and not so nice attempts. Without a doubt this one, and Kansas’s are the two best caches we have seen so far. Thank you very much for taking the time to put this together. We really enjoyed ourselves here today. [:D] TFTF </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364864187"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="96095">GuentherGal</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Mission parameters executed in tandem with Agent Fuzzy amidst a veil of secrecy today. Our objective: connect with an elusive ally and inscribe our insignia upon his classified dossier. However, unseen forces lurked in the shadows—some rogue elements from a black op, attempting to disrupt our careful choreography. They failed in their endeavor, as we emerged triumphant. Enigmatic figures, spectral visages, and clandestine whispers coalesced into a tapestry of intrigue; this operation had it all. Rest assured, we shall meticulously sanitize all intelligence to ensure our continued invisibility in the field. A splendid escapade, indeed.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364743039"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T17:28:56</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="17302140">lola3346</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTF </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364487235"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="37837318">USAdotRun</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Last cache of day 6 of our road trip from AZ to WI. This was definitely our favorite of the day. Great setup and a great hide. This was a lot of fun. So well done. Glad we made the stop to find this one.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364191311"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T10:16:02</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11853904">happybobodog</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found today with CherokeeSarah, thanks for the great cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="37.68565" lon="-85.221617"><time>2024-11-24T00:00:00</time><name>GCB0P61</name><desc>Cache Odyssey-Kentucky (Lincoln Musem TB Motel) by SwiftlyGolden</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB0P61</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey-Kentucky (Lincoln Musem TB Motel)</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="9768940" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey-Kentucky (Lincoln Musem TB Motel)</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>SwiftlyGolden</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="29835119">SwiftlyGolden</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="59" inc="1">Food nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="33" inc="1">Motorcycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="58" inc="1">Fuel nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Kentucky</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;Welcome to Cache Odyssey Journey Across America (Kentucky The Lincoln Heritage Museum). Welcome to the Blue Grass state. I hope you enjoy your visit to my home town. Make sure to check out the great museum located at this location. You may want to search out a couple of other very close by caches as well. When you do visit, make sure to bring plenty of travelers with you. There will be plenty of room to drop them off. Even some larger trackables if you have them. Let me know in your log if you are seeking out more of the Cache Odessy hides, or if this is just another hide that you found. Have fun caching!!!!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;***FTF goes to Dos-Boot&amp;amp;tiantian, AllstarSS, &amp;amp; KBLAST!!!!  Congrats!!!!!!&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Large cabinet style hide. Similar to a Little Free Library. It is on the backside of the building by the wheelchair ramp. COMBINATION # 1816</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364365809"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T10:26:19</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1906272">mdsearcher</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">No TBs in this TB Hotel.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364365209"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T10:23:12</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1906272">mdsearcher</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found this Saturday morning. Just the box by the ramp. TFTC.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364067030"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4941578">2KatzHunt</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We are on our way home from GeoWoodstock collecting the Oldest in Counties, Cache Odyssey, Webcams, and anything else that gets in our way. This was our main target for today.  We arrived to find construction all around, the county building is getting new windows. No one paid any attention to us. We found it immediately but found the lock open and just hanging there. Inside the box, we found; the log, the stamp, and a box of swag. I did not see any TBs, but I didn't go through the swag box to check. We signed the log, stamped our book, and made sure the lock was locked. This is our 15th Cache Obyssey......TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363793992"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T17:33:47</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5240023">mimandpap</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">On my way to Nashville and had to get this Cache Odyssey cache. TFTH SL </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362319371"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-20T12:08:56</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="42809914">tela42499</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Headed to geowoodstock from Asheville. This was my first stop on the way. Very nice cash. tftf from Asheville</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="19.930133" lon="-155.794133"><time>2025-06-18T00:00:00</time><name>GCB8YFB</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Hawaii 🤙🏼🌺🌋 by -DOLFINANDO-, Little_Princess22 &amp; DolfinPrincess</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB8YFB</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Hawaii 🤙🏼🌺🌋</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="10014284" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Hawaii 🤙🏼🌺🌋</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>-DOLFINANDO-, Little_Princess22 &amp; DolfinPrincess</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="42807663">DolfinPrincess</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="47" inc="1">Field puzzle</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="52" inc="0">Night cache</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="59" inc="1">Food nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="1">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="58" inc="1">Fuel nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Hawaii</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b7be9a3d-4cd6-45a8-a96e-a3a45b233f37.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;*Please do not take the stamp, this is part of the letterbox.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;This special cache celebrates Hawaii and its deep connection to the skies above. Here on the Big Island we stand on the tallest mountain on Earth when measured from base to summit. Mauna Kea rises from the floor of the Pacific and reaches higher than Mount Everest when measured in this way.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;With clear dark skies and very little light pollution, this sacred mountain is one of the finest locations on the planet for stargazing and exploring the universe. From here you can witness the Milky Way, brilliant constellations, distant galaxies, and stories written in the heavens by generations of Native Hawaiians. These skies are sacred and so is the land. Mauna Kea holds tremendous cultural and spiritual importance, where science and tradition exist together.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;The posted coordinates bring you to a sidewalk next to the bookmobile. Look toward the south and you will see an image of a girl wearing blue slippahs. The Cache Odyssey container is tucked in the spare tire compartment just below her.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;Enjoy the search and enjoy the view of the sky that has inspired explorers for centuries.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b1b969cc-4176-44a8-ae44-e0438c71e7f1.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:23pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt; geocache to &lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt; to all. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;This cache is part of the Southwest Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;!-- GeoTour links (unchanged) --&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F3"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F1"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F4"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F0"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4F2"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GT4EF"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#3498db;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:17pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6aa84f;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/b19ba586-1a55-44b3-8eb2-0781c0a8e99a.jpg" width="100%" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#222222;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Leaderboard!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;RetiredGuy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://geocachetalk.com/cache-odyssey-leaderboard/"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/88d4ab19-c51e-452e-83af-e9e74fbe1bc2.jpg" width="100%" /&gt; &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Lock Code: 7171
</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364893937"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T10:25:19</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8814283">TheLF</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Continuing my Odyssey quest after GeoWoodstock in Hutchinson, KS. I may get home in 3 weeks, and then again, I may not. I’m a geocacher and retired.😎.   This is Odyssey #44 for me.
**********
Great location and the drive  out on the 190, is representative of Hawaii off the beaten path. ❤️😎. The lava flows down over the hills were a first for me. Can’t imagine seeing them live.
Discovered 5 TBs that aren’t listed on the cache page, and retrieved 3 listed TBs to travel with, back to Florida. 
The CO contacted me in case I needed any hints on the cache. You can be sure this cache is well taken care of😎.  Thank you -DOLFINANDO- .</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364447881"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="286869">MinotRanger</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Arrived this morning in Kona on the ship Norwegian Spirit.  Took a Lyft to the airport to pick up my Enterprise rental car.  About a 40 minute drive to GZ.  Earns a favorite.  TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363646642"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="84985">FSU*Noles</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">My daughters were busy getting spa treatments at the hotel this afternoon, which gave me the chance to sneak out and grab this cache while they were all busy. When I was planning this trip I was pretty happy to see this cache was just 15 minutes away from our hotel, and had marked it as a must-find while we were here. I didn’t expect it to be this early in the week, but I’ll take what I can get! It was a fast find and I loved the hiding spot, it’s very secure and I definitely haven’t seen this technique before. The cache was in great shape and I was happy to add my name to the log today…this is my fifth Cache Odyssey and most likely my last one for a long time, as I don’t have any trips planned near any of the rest in the foreseeable future. I might have to do something about that, we’ll see! 😁 This one gets an easy favorite point from me, and I’ll include a picture of the signed logbook with this entry. TNLNSL, TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359388229"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-05T09:46:44</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3265080">cbagaason</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">At last I got cache Odyssey, Hawaii.  left two trackable picked up one all is well here it’s full of swag.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359414741"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="44381557">ShrDha</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Just as I got to the cache, who should come along but the owner of the cache!  DolfinPrincess and her dad, Dolfinando.  We had a nice visit and I introduced them to Mr. Odyssey, a visiting trackable who is trying to get to every Cache Odyssey cache.  I'll be sending him on his way this week.  His family sent me 5 trackable tags, which I attached to some of the rubber ducks from my private collection!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="47.029383" lon="-122.342667"><time>2025-12-22T00:00:00</time><name>GCBGK5Z</name><desc>Cache Odyssey - Washington by Bouncebounce</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCBGK5Z</url><urlname>Cache Odyssey - Washington</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="10242711" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Odyssey - Washington</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Bouncebounce</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="10794530">Bouncebounce</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="65" inc="1">Yard (private residence)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="47" inc="1">Field puzzle</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Washington</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e74c3c;"&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This cache is avalable between 8am and 9pm.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="color:#2ecc71;"&gt;There is parking in the driveway right next to the cache. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;If you watch my Podcast or have previously found some of my archived caches, you might recognize these puzzles. This cache consists of several of my earlier puzzles.&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;h1&gt; &lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
To access the cache tune into radio station 90.5 to get the code to the exterior lock. Use the date given on the radio for the exterior lock code. Once inside start with stage 1 to access stage 2.&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Inside stage 2 use the tool inside to access stage 3.&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Once inside stage 3 you&amp;#39;ll need to arrange the blocks in the correct order to see your four digit code to access stage 4.&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Stage 4 you will need to get the correct bison tube with the log in it.&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;The letter box stamp is in Stage 3. &lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Please make sure to put everything back in the correct locations and lock each box. &lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the Cache Odyssey! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Cache Odyssey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cache Odyssey is a thrilling, nationwide geocaching journey like no other! Conceived by some of the top cache hiders in the U.S., this adventure brings a &lt;strong&gt;unique, highly creative letterbox&lt;/strong&gt; geocache to &lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These caches are designed with &lt;strong&gt;everyone in mind&lt;/strong&gt;—from seasoned explorers to families with kids, and especially those geocaching in wheelchairs. Every cache is built to be fun, imaginative, and 100% &lt;strong&gt;accessible&lt;/strong&gt; to all.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where Can You Find Another One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here&amp;#39;s the best part—there&amp;#39;s a Cache Odyssey hide in &lt;strong&gt;every state&lt;/strong&gt;! That’s right! From coast to coast, every state in America is part of this grand adventure. Once you track down the one closest to you, why stop there?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This cache is part of the Northwest Region Geotour. There are six exciting GeoTours making up this series which include a total of 50 accessible geocaches.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Central &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, North Carolina, Ohio, Tennessee, West Virginia, and Virginia&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Midwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt; (Link to Geotour Page)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, and Wisconsin &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt; (Link to Geotour Page)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Connecticut, Delaware, Maryland, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Rhode Island, and Vermont &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northwest Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt; (Link to Geotour Page)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Alaska, Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Washington, and Wyoming &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Region GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt; (Link to Geotour Page)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana, Mississippi, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southwest Region&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;GeoTour&lt;/strong&gt; (Link to Geotour Page)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, New Mexico, Nevada, and Utah.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Odyssey Regional GeoTours Map&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;INSERT MAP&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For all you competitive geocachers who love racing to the finish line, we’ve got something just for you!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Retired Guy has put together a leaderboard for anyone who starts the journey. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Who will be the first to complete their region?&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Who will be the first to find all 50? &lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Which cache will receive the most favorite points? &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Click on the Leaderboard button to find out!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>
If you have any issue with this cache please call or text me 206-372-9680</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364108027"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T16:02:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8814283">TheLF</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Continuing my Odyssey quest after GeoWoodstock in Hutchinson, KS. I may get home in 3 weeks, and then again, I may not. I’m a geocacher and retired.😎.
**********
WOW… I hit town at rush hour, but finally arrived at GZ!  It took me a few minutes to figure out the order  to do things, but it all worked out in the end. I dropped a personal PathTag in with the log.  I like the electronic gadgets for combo ciphering also.
Favorite point for sure. Thanks for being a part of the Odyssey series.  My Odyssey #42.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364236719"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5892168">TTO2</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I can't tell you what a great pleasure it is when the CO is nearby their own Cache. Though he was supposed to be in Kansas, he wasn't and came out to greet us. I'm hoping he can join us for the group adventure next year, which we have organized, traveling to Germany, the Netherlands, and Belgium to do our top 10 favorite geocaches in each country. These caches take what he does to the next level. 

Washington State facts we learned while geocaching:

- Seattle is home to the first revolving restaurant, in 1961.
- WA state produces more apples than any other state in the union.
- WA state has more glaciers than the other 47 contiguous states combined.
- WA state’s capitol building was the last state capitol building to be built with a rotunda.
- Everett is the site of the world’s largest building, Boeing’s final assembly plant
- Medina is the home of the United States wealthiest man, Microsoft’s Bill Gates.
- The Northwestern most point in the contiguous U.S. is Cape Flattery on WA’s Olympic Peninsula.
- King county the largest county in WA was originally named after William R. King, Vice President under Franklin Pierce; it was renamed in 1986, after civil rights leader Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr.
- Microsoft Corporation is located in Redmond.
- The highest point in WA is Mount Rainier. It was named after Peter Rainier, a British soldier who fought against the Americans in the Revolutionary War.
- WA is the birthplace of both Jimi Hendrix (Seattle) and Bing Crosby (Tacoma).
- The oldest operating gas station in the United States is in Zillah.
- WA’s state insect is the Green Darner Dragonfly.
- The world’s first soft-serve ice cream machine was located in an Olympia Dairy Queen.
- Starbucks, the biggest coffee chain in the world was founded in Seattle.
- Spokane was the smallest city in size to host a World’s Fair. – 1974
- The state capital is Olympia, and the largest city is Seattle.
- As of the 2000 census, the state population was approximately 5.9 million and the state work force numbered about 3.1 million.
- Residents are called “WAians” (emphasis on the third syllable, pronounced as tone).
- Puget Sound’s many islands are served by the largest ferry fleet in the United States.
- The forests of the Olympic Peninsula are among the rainiest places in the world and the only rainforests (such as the Hoh Rain Forest) in the continental United States
- The first European record of a landing on the WA coast was by Spanish Captain Don Bruno de Heceta in 1775, on board the Santiago, part of a two-ship flotilla with the Sonora.
- The Lewis and Clark expedition entered the state on October 10, 1805.
- The first settlement in WA was New Market (now known as Tumwater) in 1846.
- In 1853, WA Territory was formed from part of Oregon Territory.
- WA became the 42nd state in the United States on November 11, 1889.
- Early prominent industries in the state included agriculture, lumber, shipping, fishing, salmon canning and mining.
- The region around eastern Puget Sound developed heavy industry during World War I and World War II, and the Boeing company became an established icon in the area.
- During World War II, Seattle was the point of departure for many soldiers in the Pacific, a number of which were quartered at Golden Gardens Park.
- In eastern WA the Hanford Works atomic energy plant was opened in 1943 and played a major role in the construction of the nation’s atomic bombs.
- In 1980, the northeast face of Mount St. Helens exploded outward, destroying a large part of the top of the volcano.
- WA is home to many innovative Internet companies, including Amazon.com, Classmates.com, Whitepages.com, and Digital Properties, LLC.
- The percentage of non-religious people in WA is the highest of any state, and church membership is among the lowest of all states.
- The state of WA is one of only seven states that does not levy a personal income tax.
- Property tax was the first tax levied in the state of WA and its collection accounts for about 30 percent of WA’s total state and local revenue.
- There are 140 public airfields in WA, including 16 state airports.
- United Airlines was originally owned by the Boeing Airplane Company.
- Popular games Pictionary, Pickle-ball, and Cranium were all invented in WA.
- Residents are called “WAians” (emphasis on the third syllable, pronounced as tone).
- The forests of the Olympic Peninsula are among the rainiest places in the world and the only rainforests (such as the Hoh Rain Forest) in the continental United States
- The first European record of a landing on the WA coast was by Spanish Captain Don Bruno de Heceta in 1775, on board the Santiago, part of a two-ship flotilla with the Sonora.
- The Lewis and Clark expedition entered the state on October 10, 1805.
- The first settlement in WA was New Market (now known as Tumwater) in 1846.
- In 1853, WA Territory was formed from part of the Oregon Territory.
- WA is one of only seven states that does not levy a personal income tax.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362959645"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4508329">JEEPocalypse</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Out caching with UnicornValkyrie today!  OMG this is my new favorite cache... I wish I could give it 10 favorite points! Thanks for an amazing find!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362950576"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="42305176">UnicornValkyrie</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTLBC!!! What an AMAZING amazing cache!!! I am so glad I got to experience this one with JEEPACOLYPSE today on our outing!!! Absolutely LOVE this!!! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362364770"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-20T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5507394">JackPenny</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC, InMemoryOf Nihongin Lady.
Signed log as JP IMO N.L.
Traded 3 TBs for 3 TBs.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="35.6075676449378" lon="-97.6095491885114"><time>2025-01-02T12:38:54</time><name>029JQCP</name><cmt>Multiple handicap parking spots</cmt><desc>Handicap Parking</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=1727ff08-ba08-47cd-8384-a9e85532c9eb</url><urlname>Handicap Parking</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="33.1258294183" lon="-96.089471271544"><time>2024-12-12T12:38:30</time><name>02AZV9M</name><cmt>Clues on the porch</cmt><desc>Virtual stage</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=ae769955-c950-41f2-adcf-82d3467f359e</url><urlname>Virtual stage</urlname><sym>Virtual Stage</sym><type>Waypoint|Virtual Stage</type></wpt><wpt lat="0" lon="0"><time>2026-02-19T12:43:35</time><name>01AZMXP</name><cmt>old location </cmt><desc>Virtual stage</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=e841fad3-ab43-4b13-9fb9-e2a037702657</url><urlname>Virtual stage</urlname><sym>Physical Stage</sym><type>Waypoint|Physical Stage</type></wpt><wpt lat="33.394533" lon="-104.529467"><time>2024-10-27T07:54:51</time><name>FNAZMXP</name><cmt /><desc>Final Location</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=d2d621f5-c639-4ddb-867c-3168ce917cbd</url><urlname>Final Location</urlname><sym>Final Location</sym><type>Waypoint|Final Location</type></wpt><wpt lat="31.2528833333333" lon="-89.8347666666667"><time>2024-12-28T19:09:03</time><name>01B0AZX</name><cmt>If you decide to use this Parking Area, approach from the South via 2nd Street using the alley.</cmt><desc>Alley Parking</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=4424bad0-fb27-4f96-bbcb-dd8e2967a7ef</url><urlname>Alley Parking</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="43.5555666666667" lon="-96.68055"><time>2024-11-23T07:06:46</time><name>P0B0MN6</name><cmt>There are a plethora of spots for all accessibility needs and during the winter this area is well maintained for any access the public may need! </cmt><desc>Handicap Parking</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=110dcf44-3518-4393-853f-416b9bd0f227</url><urlname>Handicap Parking</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="32.977258" lon="-86.357358"><time>2024-11-14T18:34:26</time><name>P0B0CFV</name><cmt>Parking lot has paved designated accessible parking spot.</cmt><desc>Lower Lot</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=206e6014-49bb-44ae-b4be-d0437a59fbb7</url><urlname>Lower Lot</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="41.428667" lon="-86.89825"><time>2024-11-07T05:15:55</time><name>01AZNR5</name><cmt>Navigate to the posted coords. You will see a depository embedded in the north wall. Enter the first word into the certitude checker to receive final instructions to find the cache.</cmt><desc>KEYWORD</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=5f3f0cb1-ccc7-447a-ba39-61f3f6243c6a</url><urlname>KEYWORD</urlname><sym>Virtual Stage</sym><type>Waypoint|Virtual Stage</type></wpt><wpt lat="0" lon="0"><time>2024-12-16T15:51:46</time><name>FNAZNR5</name><cmt /><desc>Final</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=61ebfe6b-bfcd-4024-bf54-aa6eee06eadd</url><urlname>Final</urlname><sym>Final Location</sym><type>Waypoint|Final Location</type></wpt><wpt lat="44.4985" lon="-87.994"><time>2024-12-05T19:41:03</time><name>01B0AHA</name><cmt>The best parking is on Hartung Street to the south of East Mason Street.</cmt><desc>Hartung Street</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=aa28cfcb-0355-4654-a279-b1ceea3dd2ae</url><urlname>Hartung Street</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="33.57755" lon="-81.799333"><time>2024-12-15T15:14:23</time><name>01B04VT</name><cmt /><desc>Final</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=86ed7a47-77ec-477a-8337-b4ee9fe8a717</url><urlname>Final</urlname><sym>Final Location</sym><type>Waypoint|Final Location</type></wpt><wpt lat="39.548893" lon="-79.980138"><time>2024-09-19T07:20:36</time><name>FNAY6NR</name><cmt /><desc>Final Location</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=50df37b1-dfbe-48ab-817d-57f20313490e</url><urlname>Final Location</urlname><sym>Final Location</sym><type>Waypoint|Final Location</type></wpt><wpt lat="39.548969" lon="-79.980308"><time>2024-09-19T07:20:36</time><name>P0AY6NR</name><cmt /><desc>Parking</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=b18714e6-e686-4aa7-9626-ba3389615c1a</url><urlname>Parking</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="35.6309666666667" lon="-78.9212"><time>2024-12-16T09:34:41</time><name>01AZTXN</name><cmt /><desc>Parking Lot</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=e2e75771-989e-4dee-b0c2-1f5ab84ccb2f</url><urlname>Parking Lot</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="46.612033" lon="-111.989133"><time>2024-12-20T10:33:29</time><name>01B06CE</name><cmt>Rough location of the cache inside the building. </cmt><desc>Final</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=2973f9c2-25e4-45fb-9df7-aec7db39be4d</url><urlname>Final</urlname><sym>Final Location</sym><type>Waypoint|Final Location</type></wpt><wpt lat="46.588729" lon="-112.038642"><time>2024-12-08T06:38:45</time><name>02B06CE</name><cmt>The walking mall starts here and goes a few blocks SSW. There is a parking garage just west of these coordinates. Wheelchair accessible. </cmt><desc>Walking Mall</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=81da8ced-6b62-4c71-a065-a8623115be4b</url><urlname>Walking Mall</urlname><sym>Reference Point</sym><type>Waypoint|Reference Point</type></wpt><wpt lat="46.585583" lon="-112.018433"><time>2024-12-08T06:38:45</time><name>03B06CE</name><cmt>See GC9P861 for detailed parking. Wheelchair accessible. </cmt><desc>Capitol Building</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=4e9934a4-3c73-424a-8ce2-f0246759ede5</url><urlname>Capitol Building</urlname><sym>Reference Point</sym><type>Waypoint|Reference Point</type></wpt><wpt lat="46.587633" lon="-112.034983"><time>2024-12-08T06:38:45</time><name>04B06CE</name><cmt>Free tours available. For details, visit https://mhs.mt.gov/education/ogmtours</cmt><desc>Original Governor's Mansion</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=5b363c4a-aed6-40f4-8ceb-4dcae08ddf32</url><urlname>Original Governor's Mansion</urlname><sym>Reference Point</sym><type>Waypoint|Reference Point</type></wpt><wpt lat="46.587636" lon="-112.049776"><time>2024-12-08T06:38:45</time><name>05B06CE</name><cmt>Most popular trailhead for Mount Helena.</cmt><desc>Mount Helena</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=bf16a1a1-08e0-4e2f-91fe-07e4bc2a0ae2</url><urlname>Mount Helena</urlname><sym>Reference Point</sym><type>Waypoint|Reference Point</type></wpt><wpt lat="46.614983" lon="-112.080377"><time>2024-12-08T06:38:45</time><name>06B06CE</name><cmt>Open year round, but not always fully ploughed when there is deep snow. Free admission, wheelchair accessible. </cmt><desc>Archie Bray Foundation</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=0682db19-4ea7-46a8-8715-35f7ee955316</url><urlname>Archie Bray Foundation</urlname><sym>Reference Point</sym><type>Waypoint|Reference Point</type></wpt><wpt lat="46.699167" lon="-111.811"><time>2024-12-08T06:47:32</time><name>07B06CE</name><cmt>This commemorative historic location has a wheelchair accessible, self-guided set of placards about the history of Lewis and Clark. There are also great views of the Missouri. Be advised it is not maintained in the winter, so snow and ice may be present. </cmt><desc>Two Camps Vista</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=df462deb-e3c5-4263-9399-a48ed80aaacd</url><urlname>Two Camps Vista</urlname><sym>Reference Point</sym><type>Waypoint|Reference Point</type></wpt><wpt lat="43.66025" lon="-116.409183"><time>2024-12-07T15:27:06</time><name>P1B02TT</name><cmt /><desc>Virtual stage</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=92baf7c6-84bf-410d-a95a-810d195e38fe</url><urlname>Virtual stage</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="43.661083" lon="-116.409067"><time>2024-12-07T15:27:06</time><name>P2B02TT</name><cmt /><desc>Virtual stage</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=5ecefff3-f027-4626-99cb-f66e435a8ae4</url><urlname>Virtual stage</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="36.8061493338407" lon="-76.2286001443863"><time>2024-10-13T08:48:52</time><name>P0AZ50H</name><cmt /><desc>Parking</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=329c942f-130c-49c7-b886-b075ded32068</url><urlname>Parking</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="39.7019333333333" lon="-75.5505833333333"><time>2024-11-07T11:45:39</time><name>P0B04HE</name><cmt /><desc>Parking Lot</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=89439319-9ee8-47e7-8906-1861d2cee0c3</url><urlname>Parking Lot</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="41.4782166666667" lon="-75.1838666666666"><time>2024-09-13T13:47:55</time><name>01AXXMV</name><cmt /><desc>Virtual stage</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=6b5851d2-7a6b-4c2b-95b9-9cd3834c3b6c</url><urlname>Virtual stage</urlname><sym>Physical Stage</sym><type>Waypoint|Physical Stage</type></wpt><wpt lat="40.2605833333333" lon="-74.2726666666667"><time>2024-12-27T09:39:08</time><name>RPAZ2MF</name><cmt>ADA Ramp</cmt><desc>ADA Ramp</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=9daa09af-c276-4ee6-bb90-4607f8545b0c</url><urlname>ADA Ramp</urlname><sym>Reference Point</sym><type>Waypoint|Reference Point</type></wpt><wpt lat="41.7366" lon="-71.56375"><time>2024-12-03T06:44:11</time><name>01AHEKA</name><cmt>Item where you will gather information for directions to the final </cmt><desc>Virtual stage</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=8e952286-9189-49d7-9cdb-9066cbb60799</url><urlname>Virtual stage</urlname><sym>Virtual Stage</sym><type>Waypoint|Virtual Stage</type></wpt><wpt lat="44.0040833333333" lon="-70.9926166666666"><time>2024-12-12T19:00:21</time><name>01AZTTG</name><cmt /><desc>Information sign</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=770666eb-547c-4928-bfc6-3117cd02f5d4</url><urlname>Information sign</urlname><sym>Virtual Stage</sym><type>Waypoint|Virtual Stage</type></wpt><wpt lat="36.805967" lon="-114.070383"><time>2024-11-03T17:54:46</time><name>P0B00W8</name><cmt /><desc>ADA Parking</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=9872ebc0-65f6-44fd-a8e6-dfa34d81c01f</url><urlname>ADA Parking</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="39.9962982092232" lon="-82.6747316122055"><time>2024-11-23T11:03:54</time><name>P0B0MWZ</name><cmt>Park here if on street parking is unavailable.</cmt><desc>Parking</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=9a3c5d83-3e16-4b7b-be42-0038d1f72fd8</url><urlname>Parking</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="60.55475" lon="-151.261583"><time>2024-11-11T19:31:51</time><name>FNB09MA</name><cmt>Cache is inside building lobby</cmt><desc>Cache Access Portal</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=ed9ad7eb-dbf8-4fdd-96b4-5f062753cfac</url><urlname>Cache Access Portal</urlname><sym>Final Location</sym><type>Waypoint|Final Location</type></wpt><wpt lat="39.066583" lon="-94.591283"><time>2025-01-18T18:38:46</time><name>01859C7</name><cmt>Only natural wooden structure on this side of the road.</cmt><desc>Rally Point</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=c3b46ac3-77b3-4063-bfc5-41e427772199</u